Fateless or Fatelessness ( Hungarian : Sorstalanság , lit . `` Fatelessness '' ) is a novel by Imre Kertész , winner of the 2002 Nobel Prize for literature , written between 1969 and 1973 and first published in 1975 .

Huerto Cerrado is a collection of short stories written by Peruvian author Alfredo Bryce Echenique .
Zemsta ( Revenge ) is a Polish comedy by Aleksander Fredro , a Polish poet , playwright and author active during Polish Romanticism in the period of partitions .

Windyridge is a 1912 novel by English writer Willie Riley , the first of his 39 published books .
Die Niemandsrose ( in English The No - One's - Rose ) is a 1963 German - language poetry collection by Paul Celan .

Strawberry Girl is a Newbery medal winning novel written and illustrated by Lois Lenski .
The Last Days of John Brown is an essay by Henry David Thoreau written in 1860 that praised the executed abolitionist militia leader John Brown .
Lords of the Levee is a 1943 non - fiction book by longtime Chicago Tribune reporters Lloyd Wendt and Herman Kogan in one of three collaborations about the city of Chicago , focusing on its politicians `` Bathhouse '' John Coughlin and `` Hinky Dink '' Kenna , notorious alderman for the City of Chicago 's lakeside First Ward .

An Enemy of the People ( original Norwegian title : En folkefiende ) is an 1882 play by Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen .

The Fruits of the Earth ( French : Les nourritures terrestres ) is a prose - poem by André Gide , published in France in 1897 .

The Golden Ocean is a historical novel written by Patrick O'Brian , first published in 1956 .
Beggars Ride is a 1996 science fiction novel by noted author Nancy Kress .
The Incredible Tide is a post - apocalyptic science fiction novel written by Alexander Key , published in 1970 .

`` Blumfeld , an Elderly Bachelor '' ( `` Blumfeld , ein älterer Junggeselle '' ) is an incomplete story by Franz Kafka .

The Arms of Krupp ( 1968 ) is William Manchester 's history of the Krupp dynasty , which owned and ran a dominant armaments manufacturing company in Germany .

Yellowfang 's Secret is a children 's fantasy novel written by Cherith Baldry under the pseudonym Erin Hunter .
Last of the Breed , a 1987 book by Louis L'Amour , tells the fictional story of Native American United States Air Force pilot Major Joseph Makatozi ( Joe Mack ) , shot down by the Soviets over the ocean between Russia and Alaska and then captured .

Laelius de Amicitia ( or simply De Amicitia ) is a treatise on friendship by the Roman statesman and author Marcus Tullius Cicero , written in 44 BCE .
The Disciples is a 1993 spy thriller by Joe Andrew , who was chairman of the 2000 Democratic National Convention , and V.C. Andrews .
The Future of Culture in Egypt ( Arabic : مستقبل الثقافه في مصر ‎ ) is a 1938 book by the Egyptian writer Taha Hussein .

Nosaltres , els valencians ( Valencian pronunciation : ( noˈza(ɫ)tɾes , eɫz valensiˈans ) ; `` We , the Valencians '' ) , is a historical and political essay by the Valencian ( Spain ) author Joan Fuster , first published in 1962 .
The Scorch Trials is a 2010 young - adult horror dystopian science fiction novel by James Dashner and the second book in the Maze Runner Saga .
Shot in the Heart is a memoir written by Mikal Gilmore , then a senior contributing editor at Rolling Stone , about his tumultuous childhood in a dysfunctional family , and his brother Gary Gilmore 's eventual execution by firing squad in 1977 for a convenience store murder he committed in Provo , Utah .
The Marienbad Elegy is a poem by Johann Wolfgang von Goethe .
Baby - Sitting Is a Dangerous Job is a children 's suspense novel by American author Willo Davis Roberts .
The Last Opium Den is an investigative journalism / travel book by Nick Tosches .
Bucolicum carmen is an organic collection of twelve eclogues , composed by Petrarch from c. 1346 - -7 and published in 1357 .
Anna Seghers ' novel The Seventh Cross ( German : Das siebte Kreuz ) , is one of the better - known examples of German literature circa World War II . It was published first in the United States , in an abridged version , in September 1942 by Little , Brown and Company .
Mr. Adam ( 1946 ) is the first novel written by Pat Frank dealing with the effects of a nuclear mishap causing worldwide male infertility .
Geographia Neoteriki ( Greek : Γεωγραφία Νεωτερική Modern Geography ) is a geography book written in Greek by Daniel Philippidis and Grigorios Konstantas and printed in Vienna in 1791 .

The Wild Duck ( original Norwegian title : Vildanden ) is an 1884 play by the Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen .
The Orchid Thief is a 1998 non - fiction book by American journalist and author Susan Orlean , based on her investigation of the 1994 arrest of John Laroche and a group of Seminoles in south Florida for poaching rare orchids in the Fakahatchee Strand State Preserve .
`` Golden Treasure '' is a literary fairy tale by Danish poet and author Hans Christian Andersen ( 1805 -- 1875 ) .
The Addresses to the German Nation ( Reden an die deutsche Nation , 1808 ) is a political literature book by German philosopher Johann Gottlieb Fichte that advocates German nationalism in reaction to the occupation and subjugation of German territories by Napoleon 's French Empire .
Love and Other Impossible Pursuits is a novel by Ayelet Waldman and released in 2006 .
Froth on the Daydream ( French : L'Écume des jours ; literally : `` The Foam of Days '' ) is a 1947 novel by the French author Boris Vian .
`` The Winter Market '' is a science fiction short story written by William Gibson and published as part of his Burning Chrome short story collection .
Kate Vaiden ( 1986 ) is a novel by Reynolds Price about a white woman from the American South who , after a teenage pregnancy , abandons her son shortly after giving birth to him and who does not get in touch with him for four decades .
`` I like to see it lap the Miles '' is a short poem by Emily Dickinson describing an `` iron horse '' or railroad engine and its train .
A Night in the Lonesome October is a semi - satirical , though not comic , novel by Roger Zelazny published in 1993 , near the end of his life .
The Rage and the Pride ( La Rabbia e l’Orgoglio in Italian ) is a book written in the wake of the September 11 , 2001 attacks by the late Italian journalist and author Oriana Fallaci .
Crumbling Idols is a collection of 12 essays written and completed by Hamlin Garland in 1894 .
I Know I 've Been Changed was the first major successful play from famed Gospel playwright Tyler Perry .
The Jaguar Smile is Salman Rushdie 's first full - length non - fiction book , which he wrote in 1987 after visiting Nicaragua .

The Larklight trilogy is a trilogy of young adult novels by Philip Reeve , entitled Larklight , Starcross , and Mothstorm .

Pierre et Jean is a naturalist or psycho - realist work written by Guy de Maupassant in Étretat in his native Normandy between June and September 1887 .
The Marriage of William Ashe is a novel by Mary Augusta Ward that was the best - selling novel in the United States in 1905 .
The Power of Yes is a 2009 play by English playwright David Hare .
When I Was Growing Up is an autobiographical poem written by revolutionary feminist activist , Nellie Wong in 1973 , describing her struggle to identify as an Asian - American girl growing up in the United States .

Orsinian Tales is a collection of eleven short stories by American writer Ursula K. Le Guin , most of them set in the imaginary country of Orsinia .

In Search for Khnum , a novel by writer and Egyptologist Hussein Bassir , is the first book with a Pharaonic setting among contemporary Egyptian literature in the style of `` 90s generation '' .

Emile , or On Education or Émile , or Treatise on Education ( French : Émile , ou De l’éducation ) is a treatise on the nature of education and on the nature of man written by Jean - Jacques Rousseau , who considered it to be the `` best and most important of all my writings '' .

Vladimir Vuković was awarded the International Master ( IM ) title in 1951 and International Arbiter ( IA ) in 1952 .

Parle was a 1942 ROTC graduate of Creighton University in Omaha , Nebraska .

Nicolas Chopin ( in Polish : Mikołaj Chopin ; 15 April 1771 -- 3 May 1844 ) was a teacher of French language in Prussian- and Russian - ruled Poland , and father of Polish composer Frédéric Chopin .
He was the son of David Barclay ( 1682 - -1769 ) ( `` David Barclay of Cheapside '' ) , second son of this Robert Barclay and Priscilla Freame , daughter of the banker John Freame .
He was married to Sheila MacRae from 1941 until 1967 ; the couple were the parents of four children : actresses Heather and Meredith MacRae , and sons William Gordon MacRae and Robert Bruce MacRae .
Tjamuaha ( also : Tjamuaha waTjirwe , literally English : Tjamuaha , son of Tjirwe , born ca . 1790 in Otjikune , died December 1861 in Okahandja ) was a chief of the Herero people in South - West Africa , today 's Namibia , and the father of Maharero .
Konrad Krafft von Dellmensingen ( 24 November 1862 - 21 February 1953 ) was a Bavarian Army general in World War I. He served as Chief of the General Staff of the Royal Bavarian Army before World War I and commanded the elite Alpenkorps , the Imperial German Army 's mountain division formed in 1915 .
Herbert Wittmann ( 3 January 1914 , Döllnitz -- 26 July 2007 ) was a highly decorated Oberst in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and one of only 882 recipients of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
Berthold Graßmuck was shot down by Soviet flak on 18 October 1942 over Pitomnik Airfield during the Battle of Stalingrad .

Hans Röttiger ( 16 April 1896 -- 15 April 1960 ) was a Panzer General in the German army during World War II and the first Inspector of the Army of the Bundeswehr .
Tenente colonnello Alvaro Leonardi ( 16 November 1895 -- 1 January 1955 ) was a World War I Sottotenente from Italy and a flying ace credited with eight aerial victories .
Reiner Dierksen ( 24 March 1908 -- 15 May 1943 ) was a German U - boat commander in World War II and posthumous recipient of the German Cross in Gold .
Charles Tristan , marquis de Montholon ( July 21 , 1783 -- August 21 , 1853 ) was a French general during the Napoleonic Wars .
Louis Pierre Aimé Chastel ( 29 April 1774 , Veigy , near Carouge , Savoy - 26 September 1826 , Geneva ) was a French officer in the Napoleonic Wars , who rose to lieutenant general of cavalry .
Lieutenant Rudolf Matthaei ( 10 November 1895 - -17 April 1918 ) was a World War I flying ace credited with ten aerial victories .
Joseph Chabran ( 21 June 1763 in Cavaillon -- February 1843 in Avignon ) , was a French infantry commander during the French Revolutionary Wars and the Peninsular War .
Karl Hubert Lanz ( 22 May 1896 -- 15 August 1982 ) was a German Army officer who rose to the rank of General der Gebirgstruppe ( `` General of Mountain Troops '' ) during the Second World War , in which he led units in the Eastern Front and in the Balkans .
Ernst Põdder VR I/1 ( February 10 , 1879 Aleksandri Parish , Võrumaa , Estonia - June 24 , 1932 Tallinn , Estonia ) was a famous Estonian military commander in the Estonian War of Independence .
Colonel Sir Henry Walton Ellis , KCB ( 1783 -- 20 June 1815 ) was a British soldier in the Napoleonic Wars .
Colonel Clement Biddle ( May 10 , 1740 -- July 14 , 1814 ) was an American Revolutionary War soldier .
Pietro Frugoni ( Brescia , 21 January 1851 -- Brescia , 10 July 1940 ) was an Italian General of the Kingdom of Italy who actively participated in the World War I , especially in the first four Battles of the Isonzo .
Domingo Rey d'Harcourt ( Born , Pamplona , Spain , 1883 - died , Ponts de Molins , Catalonia , Spain , February 7 . 1939 ) was a Nationalist commander during the Spanish Civil War .

33 Pegasi is the Flamsteed designation for a visual binary star in the northern constellation of Pegasus .
Upsilon Ceti ( υ Ceti , υ Cet ) is a Class K5 , fourth - magnitude star in the constellation Cetus .
Abell 39 is a low surface brightness planetary nebula in the constellation of Hercules .
HD 51799 is a red giant star in the constellation Puppis .
WD 2359 - 434 ( Gliese 915 , LHS 1005 , L 362 - 81 ) is a nearby degenerate star ( white dwarf ) of spectral class DAP5.8 , the single known component of the system , located in the constellation Phoenix , the nearest star in this constellation .
Eta Telescopii ( η Tel , η Telescopii ) , also known as HD 181296 or HR 7329 , is a star in the southern constellation of Telescopium .
Sigma Tauri ( σ Tau / σ Tauri ) is a star system in the constellation Taurus and a member of the Hyades star cluster .
HD 111597 ( Bayer designation p Centauri / p Cen ) is a star in the constellation Centaurus .
HD 96167 is an 8th magnitude G - type subgiant star located approximately 280 light years away in the constellation of Crater .
NGC 1532 is an edge - on barred spiral galaxy in the constellation Eridanus .
HD 190007 is a class K4V 7 star located in the night sky at Right Ascension 20h 02 m 47s and declination 03 ° 19′ 34 `` 43.1 in the constellation of Aquila ( constellation ) .
25 Cancri ( 25 Cnc , d2 Cancri , d2 Cnc ) is a star in the constellation Cancer .
7 Aquarii ( abbreviated 7 Aqr ) is a variable star in the constellation Aquarius .
HD 194244 is a variable Be star in the equatorial constellation of Aquila .
Messier 53 ( also known as M53 or NGC 5024 ) is a globular cluster in the Coma Berenices constellation .
Iota Geminorum ( ι Gem , ι Geminorum ) is a Class G9 , fourth - magnitude star in the constellation Gemini .
NGC 4698 is a barred spiral galaxy located around 55 million light years away from Earth in the constellation of Virgo .
OU Geminorum ( OU Gem ) is a visual binary or possible Triple star located in the constellation of Gemini .
HR 830 , also known as VZ Arietis , is an Alpha2 Canum Venaticorum variable star in the constellation Aries .
Terzan 1 is a globular cluster located around 20.000 light - years from Earth in the constellation of Scorpius , it is one of about 150 globular clusters belonging to the Milky Way .
Omicron Tauri ( ο Tau , ο Tauri ) is a star in the constellation Taurus .
R Centauri ( R Cen ) is a variable star in the constellation Centaurus .
NGC 1316 ( also known as Fornax A ) is a lenticular galaxy about 60 million light - years away in the constellation Fornax .
HR 1614 ( 284 G. Eridani , GJ 183 ) is a star in the constellation Eridanus .
NGC 4013 is an edge - on barred spiral galaxy about 55 million light - years away in the constellation Ursa Major .
HD 125288 ( Bayer designation v Cen / v Centauri ) is a star in the constellation Centaurus .
The Cartwheel Galaxy ( also known as ESO 350 - 40 ) is a lenticular galaxy and ring galaxy about 500 million light - years away in the constellation Sculptor .
Messier 41 ( also known as M41 or NGC 2287 ) is an open cluster in the Canis Major constellation .
64 Aquarii ( abbreviated 64 Aqr ) is a star in the constellation of Aquarius .
HD 20367 b is an extrasolar planet approximately 88 light years away in the constellation of Aries .
88 Tauri is a multiple star system in the Taurus constellation consisting of a total of six stars .
HD 53705/53706/53680 is a star system that lies approximately 54 light - years away in the constellation of Puppis .
WASP-48b is an extrasolar planet orbiting the star WASP-48 in the constellation Cygnus .
Knutzen Peak is a sharp , rocky summit of elevation 3,373 metres ( 11,066 ft ) standing on the north edge of Taylor Ledge in the Sentinel Range of the Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .
The Hauberg Mountains ( 75 ° 52′S 069 ° 15′W ) are a group of mountains of about 56 kilometres ( 35 mi ) extent , located 19 kilometres ( 12 mi ) north of Cape Zumberge and 48 kilometres ( 30 mi ) south of the Sweeney Mountains in Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Mount Henksen ( 66 ° 46′S 51 ° 4′E ) is an elongated mountain with several peaks , standing between Peacock Ridge and Mount Parviainen in the northern part of the Tula Mountains in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Hadley Upland ( 68 ° 29′S 66 ° 24′W ) is a triangular shaped remnant plateau with an undulating surface , 1,500 to 1,900 metres ( 4,900 to 6,200 ft ) , in southern Graham Land , Antarctica .
White Spur is the southern wall of the Allegro Valley , in the Usarp Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Greenstone Point ( 73 ° 30′S 94 ° 19′W ) is a high rock spur along the north front of the Jones Mountains of Antarctica , immediately east of Austin Valley .
The Franko Escarpment ( 83 ° 3′S 49 ° 5′W ) is a mostly snow - covered escarpment that runs north -- south for 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) and forms the northeast edge of Lexington Table in the Forrestal Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
The Brien Rocks ( 73 ° 13′S 161 ° 23′E ) are a group of prominent rock outcrops lying 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) west of the Caudal Hills , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Lagrange Island is a small rocky island 0.7 kilometres ( 0.4 nmi ) northeast of Newton Island and 3 kilometres ( 1.5 nmi ) north of Cape Mousse , Adélie Coast , Antarctica .
Fielding Col ( 68 ° 52′S 66 ° 59′W ) is an east - west trending pass between the Baudin Peaks and Hag Pike in southern Graham Land , Antarctica .
Larson Crag ( 76 ° 44′S 161 ° 8′E ) is a prominent rocky summit , over 1,600 metres ( 5,250 ft ) high , at the north end of the Staten Island Heights in the Convoy Range , Antarctica .
Mount Holt is a mountain rising to about 750 metres ( 2,460 ft ) at the terminus of Palestrina Glacier , Lazarev Bay , on Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Calf Point ( 71 ° 30′S 169 ° 45′E ) is a point between the terminus of Nielsen Glacier and Penelope Point on the west shore of Robertson Bay , northern Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Karaali Rocks ( 75 ° 22′S 137 ° 55′W ) are a small group of rocks along the east side of the mainly snow - covered Coulter Heights , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) east of Matikonis Peak in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
The Walgreen Coast ( 75 ° 30′S 107 ° 0′W ) is a portion of the coast of Antarctica between Cape Herlacher and Cape Waite , or between Bakutis Coast in the west , and Eights Coast .
Mount Franke ( 84 ° 37′S 177 ° 4′W ) is a prominent mountain , 1,600 metres ( 5,200 ft ) high , with much rock exposed on its north side , standing between Mount Wasko and Mount Cole along the west side of Shackleton Glacier in Antarctica .
Mite Skerry is a small island in the south part of the entrance to Lystad Bay , off Horseshoe Island , Antarctica .
Billycock Hill ( 68 ° 10′S 66 ° 33′W ) is a rounded , ice - covered hill in Antarctica , which rises to 1,630 metres ( 5,350 ft ) and projects 180 metres ( 590 ft ) above the surrounding ice sheet .
Mount Widerøe ( 72 ° 08′S 23 ° 30′E ) is a large mountain rising to 3,180 m between Mount Walnum and Mount Nils Larsen in the Sør Rondane Mountains on the continent of Antarctica .
Grayson Nunatak ( 76 ° 47′S 143 ° 38′W ) is a nunatak situated 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Crummey Nunatak in Antarctica .
May Glacier ( 66 ° 13′S 130 ° 30′E ) is a channel glacier about 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) wide and 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) long , flowing to the coast of Antarctica between Cape Morse and Cape Carr .
Lardeya Ice Piedmont ( Bulgarian : ледник Лардея , `` Lednik Lardeya '' \'led - nik lar-'de - ya\ ) is the glacier extending 16 km in north - south direction and 7.5 km in east - west direction on the east side of Sentinel Range in Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .

The Inaccessible Islands ( `` Islas Inaccesibles '' in Spanish ) are a group of small precipitous islands ranging from 120 to 215 m ( 394 to 705 ft ) high , the westernmost features of the South Orkney Islands , lying 20 km ( 12 mi ) west of Coronation Island in Antarctica .
Colbeck Bay ( 71 ° 38′S 170 ° 5′E ) is a cove between Duke of York Island and Cape Klovstad in the southern part of Robertson Bay , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Humphreys Ice Rise ( 67 ° 14′S 66 ° 50′W ) is an ice rise in the Muller Ice Shelf in the southwestern part of Lallemand Fjord , Loubet Coast , Antarctica .

Cape Wollaston is a cape forming the north - west extremity of Trinity Island in the Palmer Archipelago of Antarctica .
Mikado Glacier ( 69 ° 53′S 70 ° 40′W ) is a glacier on the north side of Mahler Spur , flowing west - northwest into Sullivan Glacier near the junction with Gilbert Glacier in northern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mount Borodin ( 71 ° 36′S 72 ° 38′W ) is a mainly ice - covered mountain , 695 metres ( 2,280 ft ) high , with a rock outcrop on the east side , 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) north - northeast of Gluck Peak in the southwest part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mount Breckinridge is a mountain , 2,050 metres ( 6,730 ft ) high , standing 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) south of Stor Hånakken Mountain in the Napier Mountains of Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Cape Bruce forms the northern tip of a small island lying at the eastern side of Oom Bay , separated from the mainland rocks just west of Taylor Glacier in Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica .
Green Mesa ( 77 ° 26′S 161 ° 3′E ) is an ice - free mesa of 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) extent , located 0.9 nautical miles ( 1.7 km ) west - southwest of Canfield Mesa in the western part of the Insel Range , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Herrmann Mountains ( 72 ° 33′S 0 ° 30′E ) are a group of rocky elevations including the Hamrane Heights and the Roots Heights , rising between Reece Valley and Kvitsvodene Valley in the Sverdrup Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Gruening Glacier ( 71 ° 52′S 61 ° 55′W ) is a broad glacier descending southeast between steep rock walls to the northwest part of Hilton Inlet , on the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .

Ticha Peak ( Vrah Ticha \'vr&h ' ti - cha\ ) is a 790 m peak on the east side of Omurtag Pass in Bowles Ridge , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Linehan Glacier ( 83 ° 15′S 162 ° 41′E ) is a glacier , 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long , in Antarctica .
Gavlpiggen Peak ( 73 ° 58′S 5 ° 47′W ) is a low , isolated peak 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) southwest of Klakknabben Peak , just north of the Kirwan Escarpment in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Guesalaga Peninsula is a small , L - shaped , low - lying shingle covered peninsula on the east side of Discovery Bay , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica forming the northwest coast of Iquique Cove and the north side of its entrance .
Houk Spur ( 85 ° 1′S 64 ° 45′W ) is a bare rock spur extending from the southwest side of Mackin Table , 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) north of Mount Dumais , in the southern Patuxent Range of the Pensacola Mountains in Antarctica .

Mother with Child , also known as Nurse , is an oil painting art series by Macedonian modern artist Nikola Martinoski created from the 1930s to the 1960s .
Les Joueurs de football , also referred to as Football Players , is a 1912 - 13 painting by the French artist , theorist and writer Albert Gleizes .
Ryan 's Hope is an American soap opera created by Claire Labine and Paul Avila Mayer , originally airing for 13 years on ABC from July 7 , 1975 to January 13 , 1989 .
Portrait of a Lady with a Squirrel and a Starling is a 1526 - -28 oil on tempera portrait by Hans Holbein the Younger .
Rockpalast ( Rock Palace ) is a German music television show that broadcasts live on German television station Westdeutscher Rundfunk ( WDR ) .
The Entry of the Crusaders in Constantinople ( Entrée des Croisés à Constantinople ) or `` The Crusaders Entering Constantinople '' is a large painting by Eugène Delacroix .
The Pale Horse is a work of detective fiction by Agatha Christie and first published in the UK by the Collins Crime Club on 6 November 1961 and in the US by Dodd , Mead and Company the following year .
The Holy Family with the Dragonfly , also known as The Holy Family with the Mayfly , The Holy Family with the Locust and The Holy Family with the Butterfly is an engraving by the German artist Albrecht Dürer ( 1471 - 1528 ) from approximately 1495 .
The Ninth Wave ( Russian : Девятый вал , Dyevyatiy val ) is an 1850 painting by the Russian Armenian marine painter Ivan Aivazovsky .
Morning at Grand Manan is an oil painting by Alfred Thompson Bricher .
The Dinner Party is an installation artwork by feminist artist Judy Chicago .
`` Runcible '' is a nonsense word invented by Edward Lear .
The Hours of Étienne Chevalier is an illuminated book of hours commissioned by Étienne Chevalier , treasurer to king Charles VII of France , from the miniature painter and illuminator Jean Fouquet .
Tux was created by Larry Ewing in 1996 after an initial suggestion made by Alan Cox and further refined by Linus Torvalds on the Linux kernel mailing list .

John Georgiou ( born 5 October 1975 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for St Kilda in the Australian Football League ( AFL ) during the 1990s .

Ellen Fullman ( born 1957 ) is an American composer , instrument builder , and performer .

Tinka Kurti ( born 17 December 1932 ) is one of the best known Albanian actresses .

Faith Brown ( born 28 May 1944 ) is an English actress , singer , comedienne and impressionist .

Susan Point ( born 5 April 1952 ) is a Musqueam Coast Salish artist from Canada , who works in the Coast Salish tradition .
Louis Cartier ( 1875 - -1942 ) was a famous French watchmaker and businessman known worldwide for his watch designs .

Alison Hawthorne Deming ( b. 1946 Hartford , Connecticut ) is an American poet , and essayist .

Uwe - Jens Mey ( born 13 December 1963 ) is a former speed skater , considered to be the fastest sprinter of his time because of his 500 metres supremacy in the late 1980s and early 1990s .
Caroline Webster ( born 1964 ) is an English former actress who is now a freelance film director and headshot photographer .
Netty van Hoorn ( born 14 June 1951 ) is a Dutch film director and producer who has won several awards for her work .
Geoff Pevere ( born October 1957 in Ottawa , Ontario ) is a Canadian lecturer , author , broadcaster , teacher , arts and media critic , and currently the Program Director with the Rendezvous With Madness Film Festival in Toronto .

Angelika Hoerle ( née Fick ) ( 20 November 1899 - 9 September 1923 ) was a German painter and graphic designer .

Oberst Adolf Heyrowsky , 18 February 1882 -- 1945 , was a career officer in the Austro - Hungarian military who turned to aviation .
Alexander Leslie Renton ( 6 July 1868 -- 6 May 1947 ) was a British Liberal Party and then Liberal Unionist politician .
Haakon Sandberg ( b. Haakon Philip Fretheim Aall Sandberg ; 30 August 1924 , Bergen , Norway - 30 December 2013 ) was a Norwegian film director .
Frederick Hallen ( 1 January 1859 -- 28 February 1920 ) was a Canadian - born vaudeville entertainer who found popularity on the North American stage .
Matilda , Countess of Rethel ( 1091 in Rethel -- 1151 ) was a daughter of Count Hugh I and his wife , Melisende of Crécy .
Cathal mac Finguine ( died 742 ) was an Irish King of Munster or Cashel , and effectively High King of Ireland as well .
Thomas Cooper Gotch died on 1 May 1931 of a heart attack while in London for an exhibition , and he was buried in Sancreed churchyard in Cornwall .
Len Martin ( 17 April 1919 -- 21 August 1995 ) was an Australian results reader .
Thomas Charles Lethbridge ( 23 March 1901 -- 30 September 1971 ) , better known as T.C. Lethbridge , was an English archaeologist , parapsychologist , and explorer .
Pier Francesco Orsini ( July 4 , 1523 -- 1583 ) , also called Vicino Orsini , was an Italian condottiero and patron of the arts .
Thomas Robins the Elder ( 1715 or 1716 - 1770 ) was an English artist known for his depictions of English country houses and their gardens .
Bobby Monk ( 21 January 1886 -- 19 January 1937 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Évelyne Patlagean ( 20 October 1932 -- 11 November 2008 ) was a French historian and Byzantinist , working on questions of poverty , welfare , gender , the family , and women in Byzantium .
August Agbola O'Browne ( second name also spelled as Agboola , surname as just Brown ) ( 1895 - -1976 ) was a Nigerian jazz musician by profession and is believed to have been the only black participant of the 1944 Warsaw Uprising .
Franz Xaver Gruber ( 25 November 1787 -- 7 June 1863 ) , was an Austrian primary school teacher and church organist in the village of Arnsdorf , who is best known for composing the music to Stille Nacht ( Silent Night ) .
George Frederick Cameron ( 24 September 1854 -- 17 September 1885 ) was a Canadian poet , lawyer , and journalist , best known for the libretto for the operetta Leo , the Royal Cadet .
Alberto Santana ( 1897 - -1966 ) was a Chilean screenwriter and film producer .
Habib Bacha , SMSP ( June 24 , 1931 in Tyre , Lebanon -- 23 November 1999 ) was Melkite Archbishop of the Melkite Greek Catholic Archeparchy of Beirut and Jbeil .
Wolmar Anton von Schlippenbach ( 1653 - -1721 ) was Governor General of Swedish Estonia from 1704 to 1706 .
William Tirry ( 1609 -- 12 May 1654 ) was a martyred Irish Roman Catholic priest who was beatified by Pope John Paul II for his loyalty to the church .
Kristian Magdalon Bing ( 30 May 1862 -- 6 July 1935 ) was a Norwegian jurist and mountaineer .
Eugenio Bertini ( 8 November 1846 -- 24 February 1933 ) was an Italian mathematician who introduced Bertini 's theorem .
Charlie MacKay ( 5 May 1880 -- 26 April 1953 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Kitty Gordon ( 22 April 1878 -- 26 May 1974 ) was an English stage and silent film actress .
John Woodenlegs ( 12 November 1909 - December 1981 in Billings , Montana ) was an author , educator , and the tribal president of the Northern Cheyenne from 1955 to 1968 .
Sir Joseph Aloysius Sheehy KBE ( 15 April 1900 -- 22 September 1971 ) was an Australian jurist and Senior Puisne Judge of the Queensland Supreme Court .
Pauline Vogelpoel MBE ( 24 April 1926 in Lourenço Marques , Portuguese East Africa -- 22 December 2002 in Basle , Switzerland ) was a South African arts administrator .
Colen Campbell ( 15 June 1676 -- 13 September 1729 ) was a pioneering Scottish architect and architectural writer , credited as a founder of the Georgian style .
Sir James Whitelocke SL ( 28 November 1570 -- 22 June 1632 ) was an English judge and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1610 and 1622 .
Donat Cadruvi ( 19 September 1923 -- 1 March 1998 ) was a Swiss lawyer , politician and Romansh - language writer .
Tomasz Sapieha ( 1598 -- April 1646 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth noble and politician .
Ernest Bakewell ( 1898 - -1983 ) was an English - born chemical engineer and political figure in British Columbia .

Sidi El Houari ( 1350 - -1439 ) was an Algerian imam whose real name was Ben - Amar El Houari .
Irene Joan Thirsk , CBE , FBA , FRHistS ( née Watkins ; 19 June 1922 -- 3 October 2013 ) , was a British economic and social historian , specialising in the history of agriculture .

Marie - Madeleine Jarret , known as Madeleine de Verchères ( 3 March 1678 -- 8 August 1747 ) was a woman of New France ( modern Quebec ) credited with thwarting a raid on Fort Verchères when she was 14 years old .

Paul Okesene ( 14 November 1967 -- 15 September 2012 ) was a Samoan rugby league player who represented both Western Samoa and American Samoa .
Cecil Joslin Brooks ( 1875 - -1953 ) was a British metallurgical chemist , but also collected plants ( especially ferns ) , animals , and butterflies .

John Dolman , Dowman or Dowlman ( died 1526 ) was an English clergyman and benefactor .
Matthew Thomlinson ( 1617 - -1681 ) was an English soldier who fought for Parliament in the English Civil War .
Aziz Mohammad Khan ( 1931 - -1992 ) or Aziz Qaisi was a well - known Urdu poet , short story writer , and film writer .
Frank Feller ( 1848 - 1908 ) was a Swiss artist who settled in England and made a career as an illustrator and painter .
Henry Piers , Esq ( 1568 - -1623 ) , also spelt Henry Pierce or Perse , was an Anglo - Irish landowner and Member of Parliament who held the estate of Tristernagh Abbey in the early 17th century .
Arthur Cherep - Spiridovich ( 1858 -- 22 October 1926 ) was a Russian Count who moved to the United States following the Bolshevik Revolution .
Sir Thomas Rumbold , 1st Baronet ( 15 January 1736 --11 November 1791 ) was a British politician and administrator in India , who served as Governor of Madras from 1777 to 1780 .
Petar Blagojevich ( Serbian form : Petar Blagojević/Петар Благојевић ; died 1725 ) was a Serbian peasant who was believed to have become a vampire after his death and to have killed nine of his fellow villagers .
Claude Dehombreux ( 14 October 1939 -- 31 December 2010 ) was the best Belgian rower of the 1960s--1970s , winning 30 national titles in skiff events .
Eugene Gilhawley ( 14 April 1910 -- 3 May 1987 ) was an Irish Fine Gael politician , from Ballymote , County Sligo .
Robert Bourke , 1st Baron Connemara , GCIE PC ( 11 June 1827 -- 3 September 1902 ) , was a British Conservative politician and colonial administrator .
Frank Dudley Docker CB ( 26 August 1862 -- 8 July 1944 ) , known as Dudley Docker , was an English businessman and financier .
Matthew McDiarmid , full name Matthew Purdie McDiarmid ( 25 June 1914 - -12 February 1996 ) was a Scottish literary scholar , essayist , campaigning academic and poet .
Gordon Scrutton ( 31 December 1902 -- 6 June 1966 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Sturt in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) .
Arthur St Leger , 1st Viscount Doneraile ( died 7 July 1727 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Saint Wulfram of Fontenelle or Saint Wulfram of Sens ( also Vuilfran , Wulfrann , Wolfran , Latin : Wulframnus , French : Vulfran or Vulphran ; c. 640 -- 20 March 703 ) was the Archbishop of Sens . His life was recorded eleven years after he died by the monk Jonas of Fontenelle .
Edward Chattaway ( 1873 -- 2 May 1956 ) was an English journalist and editor of The Star from 1930 to 1936 .
Johann Hofer ( 18 August 1810 in Önsbach , Baden -- 4 August 1880 in Offenburg ) was a German lawyer .
Jonathan Campbell Meakins ( 18 May 1882 -- 12 October 1959 ) was a Canadian doctor and member of the Canadian Medical Hall of Fame .
Kushimaumi Keita ( 久島海 啓太 ; 6 August 1965 -- 13 February 2012 ) , born as Keita Kushima ( 久嶋 啓太 ) , was a sumo wrestler from Shingū , Wakayama Prefecture , Japan .
Magrath Ó Fionnachta , Irish musician , died 1361 .
Claud Irvine Boswell , Lord Balmuto ( 1742 -- 22 July 1824 ) was a Scottish judge .
Cornelis Hendrikus Elleboogius ( Elleboog ) ( 1603 - -1701 ) was a Dutch Reformed theologian .
Hans Feige ( 10 November 1880 -- 17 September 1953 ) was a German General der Infantrie in the Wehrmacht during World War II .
Gerhart von Schulze - Gävernitz ( born 25 July 1864 in Breslau ; died 10 July 1943 in Krainsdorf ) was a German economist .
Turan - Mirza Kamal ( 1951 - -2004 ) was an American - born classical guitarist and composer as well as a chef .
Renate Müller ( 26 April 1906 -- 7 October 1937 ) was a German singer and actress in both silent films and sound films , as well as on stage .
Baroness Erzsébet Czobor de Czoborszentmihály ( 1572 -- 31 March 1626 ) was the second wife of Palatine György Thurzó .
Gerald Moverley ( 9 April 1922 - 14 December 1996 ) was the first Bishop of the Diocese of Hallam in Yorkshire from 30 May 1980 until July 1996 when he resigned due to ill health .
Scottish - born Thomas Bantock ( 1823 - 20 July 1895 ) was a self - made businessman and politician .
Albert Edwin Lynch ( 10 December 1900 - 23 August 1976 ) was a musician and Catholic priest .
Sir Robert Lauder of Beilmouth , Knt . , ( died 24 June 1709 ) was an armiger , lawyer and Clerk of Exchequer in Scotland .
Luis Mariano Rivera ( 1906 - 2002 ) was a Venezuelan singer , composer , poet , and dramatist .
Kahekili II , full name Kahekilinuiʻahumanu , ( c. 1737 - -1794 ) was an ali'i ( Moʻi ) of Maui .
Andries Waterboer ( c.1789 - 1852 ) was a leader ( `` kaptijn '' ) of the Griqua people .
Georg Hilker ( 5 June 1807 -- 13 January 1875 ) was a Danish decorative painter active during the Danish Golden Age in the first half of the 19th century .
Toliver Craig , Sr . ( born Taliaferro Craig ; c.1704 - -1795 ) was an 18th - century American frontiersman and militia officer .
Solomon Nunes Carvalho ( 1815 Charleston - 1897 ) was an American painter and photographer .
Harald Noreng ( 25 April 1913 -- 7 February 2006 ) was a Norwegian literary researcher and lexicographer .
Robert Bertie , 4th Duke of Ancaster and Kesteven , PC ( 17 October 1756 , Grimsthorpe -- 8 July 1779 , Grimsthorpe ) , styled Lord Robert Bertie until 1758 and Marquess of Lindsey between 1758 and 1778 , was a British peer .
Dennis Quigley ( 7 December 1913 -- 1984 ) was a Scottish professional footballer .
Edward Brereton ( c.1642 - 1725 ) , of Borras , Denbighshire , was a Welsh politician .
Elena Mumm Thornton Wilson ( 27 August 1906 -- 27 July 1979 ) was born into an unusual , wealthy , aristocratic European family and was the fourth wife of the famed American writer Edmund Wilson .
Luiz de Barros ( September 12 , 1893 -- 1982 ) was a prominent Brazilian film director , film producer , film editor , screenwriter , cinematographer , film actor and set designer and manager who played a key role in Brazilian film production from the early silent era around 1914 through to the late 1970s .
John Heylyn ( 1685 -- 11 August 1759 ) was an Anglican divine , who had a major influence on religious thought in eighteenth century England .
Marcia Ralston ( 19 September 1906 -- 23 November 1988 ) was an Australian born actress who appeared in Hollywood films in the 1930s and 1940s .
William Burchett ( 1694 - 27 December 1750 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1739 to 1750
The Dominican friar Vincent of Beauvais ( Vincentius Bellovacensis or Vincentius Burgundus ) ( c. 1190 -- 1264 ? ) wrote the Speculum Maius , the main encyclopedia that was used in the Middle Ages .
Pedro Ansúrez ( floruit 1065 - -1117 ; died 9 September 1118 ) was a Castilian count of Liébana , Saldaña and Carrión in the closing decades of the eleventh century and the opening decades of the twelfth .
Elizabeth Clarke ( c. 1565 - -1645 ) was the first woman persecuted by the Witchfinder General , Matthew Hopkins in 1645 in Essex , England .
Robert White McFarland ( June 16 , 1825-October 23 , 1910 ) was an American engineer who served as a university professor , president and Civil War officer .
Chaudhry Aftab Ahmed Gujjar died from complications of Hepatitis C and cancer in Shifa International Hospital Islamabad on 9 May 2009 , which was a biggest loss for his family members and friends , as he was sound of the people 's hearts .
Thomas Charles Bruce ( 15 February 1825 -- 23 November 1890 ) was a British barrister and a Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1874 to 1885 .
Antonio da Sangallo the Elder ( c. 1453 -- December 27 , 1534 ) was an Italian Renaissance architect who specialized in the design of fortifications .
Abigail Merwin ( 1759 - -1786 ) was a young lady in colonial era Connecticut who , in an action similar to the celebrated call to arms by Paul Revere , alerted American forces of the approach of British forces .
Joseph Kruk ( d. 1972 ) was a Polish Jewish socialist politician .
Hugo Knorr ( 17 November 1834 -- 29 September 1904 ) was a Prussian and German painter and teacher of art , specializing in landscape and marine art .
Anton Janša ( c. 20 May 1734 -- 13 September 1773 ) was a Carniolan apiarist and painter .
Berthold Hatschek ( 3 April 1854 -- 18 January 1941 ) was an Austrian zoologist remembered for embryological and morphological studies of invertebrates .
Edy Reinalter ( 24 December 1920 - 19 November 1962 ) was an Alpine skier and 1948 Olympic champion in Slalom .
Geoffrey de Saye ( 1155 - -1230 ) was an English nobleman , and Magna Carta surety .
Apoloniusz Kędzierski ( 1 July 1861 , Suchedniów -- 21 September 1939 , Warsaw ) was a Polish painter , illustrator and decorator , known for landscapes and scenes of peasant life .
Vasile Aaron ( 1770 - -1822 ) was an ethnic Romanian lawyer and poet who lived in the Austrian Empire .
Susan Sutherland Isaacs , CBE ( née Fairhurst ; 24 May 1885 -- 12 October 1948 ; also known as Ursula Wise ) was a Lancashire - born educational psychologist and psychoanalyst .
Pingali Nagendrarao ( Telugu : పింగళి నాగేంద్రరావు ) ( 29 December 1901 -- 6 May 1971 ) was a Telugu movie script writer , playwright and lyricist .
Johann Jakob Froberger ( baptized 19 May 1616 -- 7 May 1667 ) was a German Baroque composer , keyboard virtuoso , and organist .
Asbjørn Skarstein ( 7 March 1922 -- 22 October 1999 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and diplomat .
Dushun ( Chinese : 杜順 ; pinyin : Tushun ; Wade -- Giles : Tu - shun ) ( 557 - -640 ) was the First Patriarch in the Huayan School of Chinese Buddhism , which had the Indian Avatamsaka Sutra as its central scripture .
Eugene McDermott ( 1899 - 1973 ) was a geophysicist and co - founder first of Geophysical Service and later of Texas Instruments .
Major Abraham Nicholas ( died circa September 8 , 1738 ) served as mayor of Williamsburg , Virginia from 1735 to 1736 .
Frederick Gye ( the younger ) ( 1810 - -1878 ) was an English businessman and opera manager who for many years ran what is now the Royal Opera House , Covent Garden .
Percy Frank Goddard ( 27 November 1891- 8 December 1957 ) was a British boxer who became the heavyweight boxing champion in 1923 .
Einar Riis ( 19 October 1922 -- 30 May 2006 ) , was a Norwegian Consul in Rome , aircraft broker , husband of Mrs. Amelia Riis , daughter of shipowner Kristoffer Olsen .
Hajj Mirza Mohammad Karim Khan Kermani ( 1810 - 1873 ) , was a Shia scholar , a self - appointed leader of the Shaykhi community after the death of his mentor , Sayyid Kazim Rashti , who was the appointed successor to Shaykh Ahmad al - Ahsaʼi .
William Skrimshire ( the younger ) , ( 1766 in Wisbech -- 22 July 1829 ) was a surgeon and botanist .
Claude Toovey ( 24 November 1896 -- 28 January 1978 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hester Santlow ( married name Hester Booth ; c. 1690 -- 1773 ) was a noted British dancer and actress , who has been called `` England 's first ballerina '' .
Professor Yair Sprinzak ( Hebrew : יאיר שפרינצק‎ , 8 November 1911 -- 6 September 1999 ) was an Israeli scientist and politician who served as a Knesset for Moledet between 1988 and 1992 .
Sir Max Pemberton ( 19 June 1863 -- 22 February 1950 ) was a popular British novelist , working mainly in the adventure and mystery genres .
Rabbi Yaakov Gesundheit ( 1815 - 1878 ) was the chief rabbi of Warsaw from 1870 to ca .
Sir Thomas Keens ( 1870 -- 24 November 1953 ) was a British Liberal later National Liberal politician and accountant .
David Anthony Jacobs , Baron Jacobs , known as Anthony Jacobs ( 13 November 1931 -- 21 June 2014 ) was a British businessman and an Independent politician .
Ram Kapse ( 1 December 1933 -- 29 September 2015 ) was an Indian politician who was Lt Governor of Andaman and Nicobar Islands .
Alec Herd ( 8 November 1911 -- 21 August 1982 ) was a Scottish professional footballer .
İsmail Erez ( 28 September 1919 -- 24 October 1975 ) was a Turkish diplomat who held several high - ranking posts in the Turkish Foreign Service .
James Somerville , 6th Lord Somerville , ( c.1518 - 1569 ) was a Lord of the Parliament of Scotland James was the son of Hugh Somerville , 5th Lord Somerville and Jonet Maitland .
Otakar Jaroš ( Czech pronunciation : ( ˈotakar ˈjaroʃ ) ; 1 August 1912 -- 8 March 1943 ) was a Czech officer in the Czechoslovak forces in the Soviet Union .
Wang De - lu ( Chinese : 王得祿 ; pinyin : Wáng Delù ) ( 1772 - 1843 ) was a Taiwanese general during the Qing Dynasty .
José Santiago Muñoz Bezanilla ( c.1780 - 1836 ) , was a Chilean soldier and politician .
The Right Reverend Sir Thomas Gooch , 2nd Baronet ( 1674 - -1754 ) was an English bishop .
Oluf Rygh ( 5 September 1833 -- 19 August 1899 ) was a noted Norwegian archaeologist , philologist and historian .
Heinrich Carl von Schimmelmann ( 13 July 1724 -- 16 February 1782 ) was a German - born Danish nobleman , merchant and statesman .
Magdalena de la Cruz ( 1487 - -1560 ) was a Franciscan nun of Córdoba in Spain , who for many years was honored as a living saint .
René - Louis Chartier de Lotbinière ( 1641 - -1709 ) was a French - Canadian Poet , 1st Seigneur de Lotbinière in New France ( 1672 ) , Judge of the Provost and Admiralty Courts and Chief Councillor of the Sovereign Council of New France .
Jesús Aguilar Paz ( 15 October 1895 in Gualala , Santa Bárbara Department -- 26 June 1974 in Tegucigalpa ) was a Honduran chemist , pharmacist , cartographer , folklorist and teacher .
Ruth Hope Crow AM ( 1916 - -1999 ) was an Australian Political activist .
Alfred Berthoud ( 1874 - -1939 ) was a Swiss chemist , professor of chemistry at the University of Neuchâtel .
Fernando Ruiz de Castro ( d. Bayonne , 1377 ) , was a Galician nobleman of the House of Castro and prominent military figure .
Samuel Bickerton Harman ( 20 December 1819 -- 26 March 1892 ) was a Canadian lawyer , accountant , politician , civil servant , and Mayor of Toronto from 1869 - 1870 .
Nora Niland ( 26 March 1913 -- 29 December 1988 ) was Librarian and founder of the Sligo municipal art collection .
Edward Parmelee Smith ( 1827 - -1876 ) was a Congregational minister in Massachusetts before becoming Field Secretary for the United States Christian Commission during the American Civil War .
Sir George Frederick Clucas , CBE , JP ( 11 January 1870 - 11 November 1937 ) was a Manx politician and Speaker of the House of Keys from 1919 to 1937 .
Captain Pipe ( c. 1725 ? -- c. 1818 ? ) ( Lenape ) , called Konieschquanoheel and also known as Hopocan , was an 18th - century chief of the Algonquian - speaking Lenape ( Delaware ) and a member of the Wolf Clan .
Paul Friedrich Reinsch ( 21 March 1836 , Kirchenlamitz -- 31 January 1914 , Erlangen ) was a German phycologist and paleontologist .
Sir Thomas Benger Master of the Revels ( ca . 1520 ? -- March 1577 ) succeeded Sir Thomas Cawarden as Elizabeth I 's Master of the Revels on 18 January 1560 .
Franklin Thomas Backus ( 6 May 1813 -- 14 May 1870 ) was an American laywer and politician .
Arthur Balfour , 1st Baron Riverdale GCB ( 9 January 1873 -- 7 July 1957 ) , known as Sir Arthur Balfour , 1st Baronet , from 1929 to 1935 , was a British steel manufacturer .
Berchtold Haller ( c. 1492 -- 25 February 1536 ) was a German Protestant reformer .
Khan Abdul Majid Khan Tarin ( also spelt Abdul Majeed Khan ) ( 1877 - -1939 ) , Khan - Sahib , OBE , was a prominent magistrate , MLA and philanthropist of the North West Frontier Province of former British India .
Max Reichpietsch ( 24 October 1894 -- 5 September 1917 ) was a German sailor executed in 1917 for socialist agitation in the Imperial German Navy .
Charles Apthorp ( 1698 - -1758 ) was a British - born merchant in 18th - century Boston , Massachusetts .
George Fordham ( 1837 - -1887 ) was a British flat racing jockey .
James Colnett ( 1753 -- 1 September 1806 ) was an officer of the British Royal Navy , an explorer , and a maritime fur trader .
Dr. Anthony Relhan ( ca . 1715 - 1776 ) was a medical doctor and fellow of the King and Queen 's College of Physicians of Ireland , notable for writing a history of Brighton , and for promoting the drinking of mineral water .
Deric Longden ( 29 November 1936 -- 22 June 2013 ) was an English writer and autobiographer .
Wojciech Kucharski ( 1741 - -1819 ) was a Polish sculptor and mason .
Maria Curcio ( 27 August 1918 or 1919 -- 30 March 2009 ) was an Italian classical pianist who became renowned as a greatly influential and sought - after teacher .
Maurici de Sivatte i de Bobadilla ( Spanish : Mauricio de Sivatte y de Bobadilla ) ( 1901 - 1980 ) was a Spanish Carlist politician
Salik Lucknawi ( 16 December 1913 -- 4 January 2013 ) was the nom de plume of Shaukat Riaz Kapoor , an Indian Urdu poet and journalist .
John Wesley Hales ( Ashby de la Zouch , Leicestershire , Oct. 5 , 1836-London , May 19 , 1914 ) , was a British scholar and man of letters .
Mary Chudleigh , Lady Chudleigh ( August 1656 -- 1710 ) was an English poet who was part of an intellectual circle which included Mary Astell , Elizabeth Thomas , Judith Drake , Elizabeth Elstob , Lady Mary Wortley Montagu , and John Norris .
Christoph von Stadion ( 1478 - -1543 ) was Prince - Bishop of Augsburg from 1517 to 1543 .
Milton Kohn ( died 2001 ) was one of the leading private collectors of Holocaust memorabilia , and at one point had the world 's largest collection of Holocaust memorabilia .
Cecilia May Gibbs MBE ( 17 January 1877 -- 27 November 1969 ) , publishing under the name May Gibbs , was an English Australian children 's author , illustrator , and cartoonist .
Helen Lyman commonly known as Helen Hoyt or Helen Hoyt Lyman ( January 22 , 1887 -- August 2 , 1972 ) was an American poet .
Ludwig Babenstuber ( 1660 -- 5 April 1726 ) was a German philosopher and theologian and vice - chancellor of the University of Salzburg .
Henryk Lederman , ( nom - de - guerre `` Heniek '' ) ( born ? , died September 5 , 1944 in Warsaw ) - Cadet officer of the Polish Army , participant in the Warsaw Ghetto Uprising and the Warsaw Uprising .
Edith MacGregor Rome , RRC , SRN ( died 6 June 1938 ) was a British nursing matron and administrator .
Stefan Czarniecki ( ˈstɛfan t͡ʂarˈɲɛt͡skʲi ) of the Łodzia coat of arms ( 1599 -- 16 February 1665 ) was a Polish nobleman , general and military commander .
John Ker ( 8 August 1673 -- 8 July 1726 ) was a Scottish spy during the Jacobite risings .
Lieutenant Colonel Asrat Desta ( died 3 February 1977 ) was a member of the Derg , the military junta that ruled Ethiopia during the Ethiopian Revolution .
Enoch Douglas Davis ( 1908 - -1985 ) was an American reverend , author and civil rights activist who spent the majority of his life in the town of St. Petersburg , Florida .
Alf Goullet ( 5 April 1891 -- 11 March 1995 ) was an Australian cyclist who won more than 400 races on three continents , including 15 six - day races .
Joseph Moretti ( died 1 May 1793 ) was a German architect of Italian birth of the late baroque era .
D. M. Sutherland ( ? -- 13 December 1951 ) was a British journalist and editor .
Edwin G. Waite ( died 30 October 1894 ) was a politician , newspaper man , author , and goldminer .
Michał Twaróg of Bystrzyków ( Polish : Michał Twaróg z Bystrzykowa ; Latin : Michael vulgo Parisiensis de Majori Bystrzyków ) ( ca . 1450 - -1520 ) was a Polish philosopher and theologian of the early 16th century .
Vere Essex Cromwell , 4th Earl of Ardglass PC ( I ) , ( 2 October 1625 -- 26 November 1687 ) was an English nobleman , son of Thomas Cromwell , 1st Earl of Ardglass and Elizabeth Meverell .
James Hoste ( 1633 - -1699 ) , of Wood Hall , Sandringham , Norfolk , was an English politician .
Ambika Dutt Ranga ( 19 September 1919 -- 10 January 1990 ) was an Indian footballer .
Bayume Mohamed Husen ( born Mahjub bin Adam Mohamed ; 22 February 1904 -- 24 November 1944 ) was son of a former askari officer and served together with his father in WW I with German colonial troops .
Juan de Lima Serqueira ( c. 1655 - 1726 ) was a Spanish Baroque composer of tonos humanos .
Geoffrey Burnand ( 1 January 1912 -- 17 August 1997 ) was an English painter , theatrical designer and mural artist .
Karl Koopman ( 1 April 1920 -- 22 September 1997 ) was a zoologist with a special interest in bats .
James Mourilyan Tanner ( 1 August 1920 -- 11 August 2010 ) was a British pediatric endocrinologist who was best known for his development of the Tanner scale , which measures the stages of sexual development during puberty .
John Riley Holt , FRS ( 15 February 1918 -- 6 January 2009 ) was an English experimental physicist who played a part in the development of the atom bomb and later became one of the pioneers of elementary particle physics research .
Konrad Meyer or Konrad Meyer - Hetling ( 15 May 1901 -- 25 April 1973 ) was a German agronomist .
Ivan Mavrodi ( Russian : Иван Мавроди ; 5 August 1911 , Katarzhino -- 1981 , Odessa ) was a Bulgarian - Ukrainian Soviet writer and poet .
John Blight ( 30 July 1913 -- 1995 ) was an Australian poet of Cornish origin , his ancestors having arrived in South Australia on the Lisander , in 1851 .
Nicolas Trigault ( 1577 - -1628 ) was a Walloon Jesuit , and a missionary to China .
Stanislas Anselmetti ( 1892 -- 18 August 1952 ) was a Swiss racewalker .
Annie Landouw ( also Landauw , 1913 -- 17 August 1982 ) was an Indonesian keroncong singer and film actress .
Micajah C. Henley ( 1856 - -1927 ) was a Richmond , Indiana industrialist and inventor .
Browder J. Thompson ( August 14 , 1903 -- July 4/5 , 1944 ) was a noted American electrical engineer .
Tarlton made his last will on 3 September 1588 , describing himself as ' Richard Tarlton , one of the Grooms of the Queen 's Majesty 's Chamber ' .
( Emma Judith ) Mary Forster ( 1853 - -1885 ) was a British water - colour painter .
Daniel Penfield ( 1759 -- 1840 ) was an American merchant and Revolutionary War veteran who is best known for founding the town of Penfield , New York .
Sukarni ( 14 July 1916 - 7 May 1971 ) was one of young Indonesian activists who demanded independence during Dutch colonial governments and Japanese imperial army occupation and the chairman of Murba until his death .
Piotr Dunin ( c. 1415 -- 1484 ) was a Polish leader .
Rich Brenner ( 1946 -- 2012 ) was a graduate of Baldwin - Wallace College in Berea , Ohio .
Henry Coldston or Goldstone ( by 1498 - 1547 ) , was an English politician .
Carl August Nicholas Rosa ( 22 March 1842 -- 30 April 1889 ) was a German - born musical impresario best remembered for founding an English opera company known as the Carl Rosa Opera Company .
Philipp Rupprecht ( 4 September 1900 -- 4 April 1975 ) was a German cartoonist best known for his antisemitic caricatures in the Nazi publication Der Stürmer , under the pen - name Fips .
Haring Harinxma ( 1323 - -1404 ) was a powerful Frisian chieftain and Schieringer who lived during the 13th and early 14th centuries .
Bruno Ryves ( 1596 - -1677 ) was an English royalist churchman , editor in 1643 of the Oxford newsbook Mercurius Rusticus , and later dean of Chichester and dean of Windsor .
Josef Odložil ( Czech pronunciation : ( ˈjozɛf ˈodloʒɪl ) ; 11 November 1938 -- 10 September 1993 ) was a Czech middle - distance runner .
Mary Desha ( 1854 - -1911 ) was a founder of Daughters of the American Revolution .
Sir William Williams , 1st Baronet , Kt ( 1634 -- 11 July 1700 ) was a Welsh lawyer and politician .
Robert Murray Gilchrist ( 6 January 1867 -- 1917 ) was an English novelist and author of regional interest books about the Peak District .
John Butler of Clonamicklon ( or of Lismalin ) , ( 1305- January 6 , 1330 ) was the youngest son of Edmund Butler , Earl of Carrick and Joan FitzGerald .
Blessed Buenaventura García de Paredes ( Castañedo de Valdés April 19 , 1866 - 1936 ) was a Dominican priest and Master of the Order of Preachers .
Hemminki of Masku ( Finnish : Hemminki Maskulainen , Hemming Henrikinpoika Hollo ; Latin : Hemmingius Henrici ; c. 1550 - -1619 ) was a Finnish priest , hymn writer , and translator .
Sydney Starr ( Kingston upon Hull 10 June 1857 - New York City , 3 March 1925 ) was an English painter .
Loïc Leferme ( 28 August 1970 - -11 April 2007 ) was a French diver who was the world free diving record holder until 2 October 2005 , when he was surpassed by Herbert Nitsch .
Alphonse Kann ( 14 March 1870 -- 1948 ) was a prominent French art collector of Jewish heritage .
Wouter Gysaerts or Gualterus Gysaerts ( 1649 -- in or after 1677 ) was a Flemish still life painter who specialized in flower pieces and garlands .
Edward Dayes ( 1763 - -1804 ) was an English watercolour painter and engraver in mezzotint .
Harry Dewse ( 23 February 1836 -- 8 July 1910 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played one match for Yorkshire County Cricket Club , against Middlesex at the Prince 's Cricket Ground , Chelsea in May 1873 .
George Hamond ( 1620 - -1705 ) was an English ejected nonconformist minister .
Major General Colin Hall Simpson , CBE , MC , VD ( 13 April 1894 -- 23 August 1964 ) was an Australian Army officer who rose to the rank of major general as Signal Officer in Chief during the Second World War .
Hannah Margaret Mary Closs ( 1905 - 1953 ) was an art critic and novelist .
Christopher Feake ( 1612 - -1683 ) was an English Independent minister and Fifth - monarchy man .
Ye Yuanlong ( simplified Chinese : 叶元龙 ; traditional Chinese : 葉元龍 ; pinyin : Yè Yuánlóng ; 1879 - 1967 ) was a Chinese educator and economist .
Pope Leo VI ( died February 929 ) was Pope for just over seven months , from June 928 to his death in February 929 .
Dick Upex ( 26 June 1892 -- 22 May 1979 ) was an English professional football inside left who played in the Football League for Charlton Athletic .
Lajos Abafi or Ludwig Abafi - Aigner ( 11 February 1840 , Nagyjécsa , Torontál Shire -- 19 June 1909 , Budapest ) was a Hungarian editor , a librarian and entomologist .
