Sir Thomas Monson , 1st Baronet ( 1565 -- 29 May 1641 ) was an English politician and supporter of King James I.
Canon Horace Newton ( Born 1844 , Died 1920 ) was a priest within the Church of England , philanthropist , and country landowner .
Sir Alexander Fraizer ( 1610?--1681 ) , was a Scottish physician .
Benjamin Edward Spence ( 1822 - -1866 ) was an English sculptor , who spent much of his professional life in Italy
Hayyim ben Judah ibn Musa ( Béjar , near Salamanca 1380 - 1460 ) was a Jewish physician , chemist , astronomer , and apologist who contended with Nicholas de Lyra .
Sir Robert Dillington , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1575 - 1664 ) was an English aristocrat of the Dillington baronets , grandfather to Sir Robert Dillington , 2nd Baronet .
Helen Sutermeister ( 1943 or 1944 - 1979 ) was a historian and archaeologist involved in the program of Industrial Archaeology in Ontario .
Thomas Russ Deacon ( 3 January 1865 -- 30 May 1955 ) was a Canadian politician , the 24th Mayor of Winnipeg in 1913 and 1914 .
Áskell Löve ( 20 October 1916 - 29 May 1994 ) was an Icelandic systematic botanist , particularly active in the Arctic .
Arthur Forbes , 9th Earl of Granard AFC ( 1915 - 21 November 1992 ) , was a British peer .
Charles Compton , 7th Earl of Northampton , DL ( 22 July 1737 -- 18 October 1763 ) was a British peer and diplomat .
José Augusto Ferreira Veiga , Viscount of Arneiro ( 22 November 1838 -- 1903 ) was a Portuguese composer .
Douglas M. Thornton ( 1873 - -1907 ) was an English Christian missionary to Cairo , Egypt with the Church Missionary Society from 1898 - 1907 .
Oliver Byrne ( 26 July 1944 in Dublin -- 26 August 2007 ) was formerly the CEO of Irish soccer club Shelbourne F.C ..
Robert Goble ( 1903 - -1991 ) was an English harpsichord builder .
Baron Gaston van de Werve et de Schilde ( 22 March 1867 -- 18 August 1923 ) was a Belgian Roman Catholic politician .
Herman G. Weinberg ( 9 August 1908 -- 7 November 1983 ) was an American subtitler , film journalist and author .
Dr . Yashwant Singh Parmar ( 4 August 1906 -- 2 May 1981 ) was an Indian politician .
Alfred Marshall ( 26 July 1842 -- 13 July 1924 ) was one of the most influential economists of his time .
Karl Langer , Ritter von Edenberg ( 15 April 1819 , Vienna - 8 December 1887 ) was an Austrian anatomist .
Enrico Zuccalli , ( Johann Heinrich Zuccalli ; ca . 1642 -- 8 March 1724 ) was a Swiss architect who worked for the Wittelsbach regents of Bavaria and Cologne .
Sir Barry Denny , 1st Baronet ( c. 1744 -- April 1794 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician .
Reinhold Lepsius ( 14 June 1857 -- 16 March 1922 ) was a German painter , especially of portraits , and graphic artist .
William de Leftwich Dodge ( 1867 - -1935 ) was an American artist best known for his murals , which were commissioned for both public and private buildings .
Henry Hakewill ( 4 October 1771 -- 13 March 1830 ) was an English architect .
Lárentíus Kálfsson ( medieval Icelandic Laurentius Kálfsson ; 10 August 1267 -- 16 April 1331 ) was bishop of the northern Icelandic diocese of Hólar 1324 - -31 .
Eugene Mailloux ( 1878 in Stoney Point , Ontario -- 1929 ) was the founder and president of M & P grocery and meat stores in the early 1900s .
Beatrice Plummer , Baroness Plummer ( 14 April 1903 - 13 June 1972 ) was a British peeress .
Heneage Finch , 5th Earl of Winchilsea FSA ( 1657 -- 30 September 1726 ) was an English peer , styled Hon . Heneage Finch until 1712 .
Bea Orpen HRHA ( 7 March 1913 -- 12 July 1980 ) was an Irish landscape and portrait painter and teacher .
Wesley Wait ( May 15 , 1861 -- July 16 , 1949 ) was an American inventor , author , dental surgeon , and florist .
Jan Nowak - Jeziorański ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈjan ˈnɔvak jɛʑɔˈraɲskʲi ) ; 2 October 1914 -- 20 January 2005 ) was a Polish journalist , writer , politician , social worker and patriot .
Juan Alonso Pérez de Guzmán y Coronel ( 1285 - 1351 ) , second lord of Sanlúcar , was a Castilian noble of the house of Medina Sidonia .
Jenny Boult ( 8 October 1951 -- 1 November 2005 ) , also known as MML Bliss , was an Australian poet , playwright , and editor .
Roy Payne ( 7 October 1909 -- 22 August 1969 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hao Pengju ( simplified Chinese : 郝鹏举 ; traditional Chinese : 郝鵬舉 ; pinyin : Hǎo Péngjŭ ; Wade -- Giles : Hao P'eng - chü ; January 29 , 1903 -- 1947 ) was a general and governor of Huaihai province of the Republic of China .
Alby Why , known by the alias Alby Carr , ( 1899 - 1969 ) was an Australian rugby league player of the 1920s player for the South Sydney Rabbitohs , who played under his alias for most of his career .
Guillaume Blanchard ( 1650 -- 1716 ) was an early settler at Annapolis Royal , Nova Scotia at a site on the Petitcodiac River .
Jeremy Brett ( born Peter Jeremy William Huggins ; 3 November 1933 -- 12 September 1995 ) , was an English actor , probably best known for playing fictional detective Sherlock Holmes in four Granada TV series from 1984 to 1994 in all 41 episodes .
Faustino Galicia Chimalpopoca or Faustino Chimalpopoca(tl ) Galicia ( died 1877 ) was the most active scholar of the Nahuatl language of the 19th century .
Sir Edwin Saunders ( 1814 -- 15 March 1901 ) was Queen Victoria 's personal dentist , and the first dental surgeon to be knighted .
Sir William Cockburn , 11th Baronet ( 2 June 1773 - 30 April 1858 , Kelston ) was a Church of England clergyman .
Pitts Sanborn ( 1879 - -1941 ) , was born John Pitts Sanborn in Port Huron , Michigan .
Amalia Sánchez Ariño ( 1883 - -1969 ) was a Spanish - born Argentine stage and film actress .
Edward Francis Cunningham ( ca . 1742 - -1795 ) , sometimes called Kelso or Francesco Calza or Calze , was a Scottish portrait painter .
Alfred Eddison Hutton ( 31 December 1865 - - 30 May 1947 ) was a British Liberal politician and manufacturer .
Margareta Clausdotter ( died 10 December 1486 ) was a nun and was , from 1473 until her death , abbess of the Bridgettine Abbey of Vadstena .
Ela Peroci ( 11 February 1922 -- 18 November 2001 ) was a Slovene children 's writer , author of numerous children 's stories that are considered classics in Slovene children 's literature .
Agnar Bachen ( 1922 - -1996 ) was a Norwegian , later naturalized British ship captain .
Friedrich Geiger ( 24 November 1907 -- 13 June 1996 ) was a German automobile designer whose most notable cars , the pre - World War II Mercedes - Benz 540 K and post - war Mercedes - Benz 300SL , are among the most highly regarded in automotive history .
Eva Sophie Piper , née Eva Sophie von Fersen ( 30 March 1757 -- 2 February 1816 , Löfstad Slott ) was a Swedish countess and lady in waiting .
William Fenner ( 1600 - -1640 ) was an English Puritan divine .
Francesco Longo Mancini ( 1880 - -1954 ) was an Italian painter of the early 20th century who was known for his paintings of nudes .
Shirley Rumsey ( 1933 - 1996 ) was an English musician who recorded two well - received solo CDs of Renaissance music for Naxos Records in the mid 1990s .
Robert Christopher Tytler ( 25 September 1818 -- 10 September 1872 ) was a British soldier , naturalist and photographer .
Edward Cracknell ( 1831 -- 14 January 1893 ) was New South Wales superintendent of telegraphs .
John Delap ( 1725 - -1812 ) was an English churchman and academic , known as a poet and dramatist .
Jan Aronsson ( 28 November 1931 -- 4 January 2016 ) was a Swedish footballer .
Øystein Elgarøy ( 1929 - -1998 ) was a Norwegian astronomer , with a specialty in solar radio astronomy .
Sir William Spring , 1st Baronet ( 1613 -- 17 December 1654 ) was an English Parliamentarian politician and a member of the Spring family of Pakenham , Suffolk .
Robert Wight ( 6 July 1796 -- 26 May 1872 ) was a Scottish surgeon and botanist who spent 30 years in India .
James Hurdis ( 1763 - -1801 ) was an English clergyman and a poet , born in Bishopstone , East Sussex .
Nelly Blair , later Nelly Smith ( 1759 -- 1820 ) .
Heikki Simonen ( 22 April 1902 , Alavieska - 16 January 1975 ) was a Finnish smallholder and politician .
Devyani Chaubal ( 1942 -- 13 July 1995 ) was an Indian journalist and columnist .
Kim Saryan or Kim Sa - ryang ( Japanese 金 史良 キム・サリャン Korean 김 사량 ) ( March 3 , 1914 -- 1950 ) was a Japanese and Korean author during the Japanese Colonial Period .
Frank Arthur Bellamy ( 17 October 1863 -- 15 February 1936 ) was a British astronomer worked on Astrographic Catalogue with his niece , Ethel Bellamy .
Ramaprasad Banik ( ? --2010 ) was a Bengali theatre actor , director and playwright .
Alvin Todd ( 23 January 1903 -- 27 June 1964 ) , was an American film editor .
Ranbir Singh Kanwar(b . Dec. 20 , 1930 ; d. Dec. 20 , 2005 ) was an eminent plant breeder and agronomist who helped usher in the green revolution in India ( http://www.sugarcaneindia.com/r_s_kanwar.html ) .
Sir Maurice de Berkeley `` the Resolute '' ( 1218 - 4 April 1281 ) , 5th ( feudal ) Baron de Berkeley , was an English soldier and rebel , residing at Berkeley Castle in the English county of Gloucestershire .
Girolamo Lucchesini ( 7 May 1751 -- 20 October 1825 ) was a diplomat of the Kingdom of Prussia .
Basheer Mauladad ( 1931 - 2014 ) was a prominent Kenyan Asian .
Richard Fermor ( 1480x84 - -1551 ) , was an English wool merchant .
Rolo Mestman Tapier ( 1 July 1945 -- 3 December 2007 ) otherwise known as Lord Bloody Wog Rolo was a colourful eccentric Sydney identity and one of the founding members of BUGAUP ( Billboard Utilising Graffitists Against Unhealthy Promotions ) .
Ian B. Tanner ( 24 February 1926 - 27 December 2013 ) was an Australian Presbyterian and Uniting Church minister .
Clarance Holt ( 9 January 1826 -- 27 September 1903 ) , born Joseph Frederick Holt was an English actor - manager who had a successful career on the stage in England , Australia and New Zealand .
Henry Andres Burgevine ( Chinese : 白齊文 ) ( 1836 - -1865 ) was an American sailor of French ancestry , mercenary and soldier of fortune , who became famous for his military victories for Imperial China during the Taiping Rebellion .
George Samuel Sewell GM and bar ( 26 September 1897 -- 5 April 1969 ) was one of the first recipients of the George Medal ( GM ) and was the first civilian to be awarded a bar to the GM .
Theresa Yelverton ( 1833 -- 13 September 1881 ) was an English woman who became notorious because of her involvement in the Yelverton case , a 19th - century Irish law case , which eventually resulted in a change to the law on mixed religion marriages in Ireland .
Dom Benet Perceval , OSB ( 1916 -- 2009 ) was the oldest member of the monastic community at Ampleforth Abbey , England , when he died at age 92 on 30 January 2009 .
Arwel Hughes OBE ( 25 August 1909 -- 23 September 1988 ) was a Welsh orchestral conductor and composer .
Levi Gibbon ( c. 1807 -- 1 August 1870 ; `` Lefi Gibbwn '' in Welsh ) was a Welsh balladeer .
Cristián Huneeus ( 1935 - -1985 ) was a Chilean essayist and writer .
Thomas Henry Tizard C.B , F.R.S , R.N ( 1839 -- 17 February 1924 ) , was an English oceanographer , hydrographic surveyor , and navigator .
John Grainger ( 1830 , Belfast-- 1891 ) was an Irish cleric and antiquarian .
Anton Flettner ( November 1 , 1885 December 29 , 1961 ) was a German aviation engineer and inventor .
Nathaniel Vincent ( c.1639?--1697 ) was an English nonconformist minister , ejected in 1662 and several times imprisoned .
Joseph William Dunning ( 5 November 1833 , Leeds -- 15 October 1897 , London ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera .
Zhu Shuzhen ( Chinese : 朱淑真 , ) ( c. 1135 -- 1180 ) was a Chinese poet who lived during the Song dynasty .
Mary Maguire ( 22 February 1919 -- 18 May 1974 ) was an Australian - born actress who briefly became a Hollywood and British film star in the late 1930s .
Mairtin Thornton ( died 1984 ) was an Irish heavyweight boxer in the 1940s .
Olav Bjaaland ( 5 March 1873 -- 8 June 1961 ) was a Norwegian ski champion from Telemark .
Reinhold Grönvall ( 1 May 1851 , Pori - 3 March 1916 ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman .
Chang Chi - yun ( Chinese : 張其昀 ; pinyin : Zhāng Qíyún ; 29 September 1901 -- 26 August 1985 ) was a historian , geographer , educator and politician .
Hemi Topine Te Mamaku ( c. 1790 -- June 1887 ) was a Māori chief in the Ngāti Hāua - te - rangi iwi from the Whanganui region of New Zealand 's North Island .
Walter Gempp ( 13 September 1878 - 2 May 1939 ) was a firefighting expert .
Sir Robert Catlyn ( died 1574 ) was an English judge and Chief Justice of the Queen 's Bench .
Anthony Wotton ( c. 1561 -- 1626 ) was an English clergyman and controversialist , of Puritan views .
Alaviyya Babayeva Hanifa Kizi ( 12 August 1921 -- 23 September 2014 ) was a prose - writer , translator of contemporary Russian literature , and publicist .
James Kilton Clapp ( December 30 , 1897 -- 1965 ) was an American electrical engineer who worked for General Radio Corporation .
Beaumont Cranfield ( 28 August 1872 -- 20 January 1909 ) was an English professional cricketer who played first - class cricket for Somerset County Cricket Club and the Marylebone Cricket Club ( MCC ) between 1897 and 1908 .
Élie Le Goff was a French sculptor born in 1858 and who died in 1938 .
Mircea Grabovschi ( sometimes spelled Grabovski or Grabowski ; December 22 , 1952 - -2002 ) was a Romanian handball player and coach .
Conall mac Taidg ( died c. 807 ) ( Conall son of Tadc ) was a king of the Picts from 785 until 789 .
Peter Perchard ( c. 1729 - 21 January 1806 ) was a British goldsmith and merchant who served as Lord Mayor of London in 1804 .
László Palóczy ( 14 October 1783 -- 27 April 1861 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as acting Speaker of the House of Representatives as oldest member of the lower house in 1849 .
Jeong Ki - ryong ( 1562 - -1622 ) was a prominent Korean Army general during the Joseon Dynasty .
George IV , Count of Erbach - Fürstenau ( 12 May 1646 -- 20 June 1678 ) , was a member of the German House of Erbach who held the fiefs of Fürstenau , Michelstadt , Reichenberg , Bad König and Breuberg .
Baptist Noel , 4th Earl of Gainsborough ( 1708 -- 21 March 1751 ) was an English peer and Member of Parliament , styled Viscount Campden until 1714 .
Walter Süskind ( 29 October 1906 -- 28 February 1945 ) was a German Jew who helped about 600 Jewish children escape the Holocaust .
Henry Stephen Gorham(1839 - -1920 ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Coleoptera .
Artie Gold ( 15 January 1947 -- 14 February 2007 ) was a Montreal based Canadian poet who rose to prominence in the 1970s as one of the circle of Montreal - based writers known as The Vehicule Poets .
Robert of Thornham ( or Robert de Turnham ) ( died 1211 ) was an English soldier and administrator .
Henrich Krummedige ( also recorded as Hinrik , Henrik or Henry with surname variations including Krummedike and Krummendiek ) , was born circa 1464 in Norway and died in 1530 .
Charles John Prescott ( 9 June 1857 -- 12 June 1946 ) was an English born Australian army chaplain , Methodist minister and headmaster .
Sima Daozi ( 司馬道子 ) ( 364 - -403 ) , formally Prince Wenxiao of Kuaiji ( 會稽文孝王 ) , was a regent during the reign of his nephew Emperor An of Jin , being the younger brother of Emperor Xiaowu .
Lakshman Rajapaksa ( 1905 - -1969 ) also known as D. A. Rajapaksa , was a Sri Lankan politician .
Hillson Beasley ( 30 April 1855 -- 7 October 1936 ) was an English - trained architect who relocated to Australia , executing his major buildings in Melbourne ( 1886 - -96 ) and Perth ( 1896 - -1917 ) .
Horace Evans , 1st Baron Evans ( 1 January 1903 -- 26 October 1963 ) was a Welsh physician who served the royal family of the United Kingdom .
Ruth A. Myers ( 1926 - -2001 ) was known as the `` grandmother of American Indian Education in Minnesota . ''
George Simmonds ( 16 July 1895 -- 15 January 1973 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Nevell , Neville , Nevill or Nevil , ( ? - 1697 ) , was an English Vice Admiral from the 17th century .
Louis - François Roubiliac ( more correctly Roubillac ) ( 1702/1705 -- 11 January 1762 ) was a French sculptor who worked in England , one of the four most prominent sculptors in London working in the rococo style , He was described by Margaret Whinney as `` probably the most accomplished sculptor ever to work in England '' .
Johann Spies ( ca . 1540 - 1623 ) was a German printer who published an anonymous book of tales about a legendary Doctor Faust who made a pact with the Devil .
Leela Dube ( 27 March 1923 -- 20 May 2012 ) was a renowned anthropologist and feminist scholar , fondly called Leeladee by many .
John William Kirwan ( died 29 December 1849 ) was the first President of Queen 's College , Galway .
Mehmed I Giray , Mukhamad Khan Girai , known as Great ( 1465 - -1523 ) -- a khan of the Crimean Khanate in 1515 --1523 .
Tzimtzincha - Tangaxuan II ( died 1530 ) was the last cazonci ( monarch ) of the Tarascan state , the kingdom of the Purépecha from 1520 - -1530 .
Margaret Battye ( 9 August 1909 -- 16 November 1949 ) was an Australian barrister and jurist , who is considered as one of the most influential women in politics , business and the legal advancement in Oceania .
Mauro Aldrovandini ( 1649 - -1680 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
Gertie Gitana ( 27 December 1887 -- January 1957 ) was a British music hall entertainer .
Hernando Pizarro Leongómez ( 1959 - 25 February 1995 in Bogotá ) was a Colombian guerrilla , not only known for being the brother of the commander of the 19th of April Movement ( M-19 ) Carlos Pizarro Leongómez but as the second in command of the Ricardo Franco Front .
Rotmistrz Ryszard Dembinski ( 24 February 1924 -- 29 June 2008 ) was a Polish Cavalry officer and D - Day Veteran , who , following World War II , helped to establish the Polish Institute and Sikorski Museum in London , which he chaired for 25 years ( 1979 - -2004 ) .
Paddy Tunney ( 28 January 1921 -- 7 December 2002 ) was an Irish traditional singer , poet , writer , raconteur , lilter and songwriter .
Rudolf Callmann ( 29 September 1892 -- 12 March 1976 ) was a German American legal scholar .
Agnes , Countess of Dunbar and March ( née Randolph ; c. 1312 - -1369 ) , known as Black Agnes for her dark hair and eyes , and sallow complexion , was the wife of Patrick , 9th Earl of Dunbar and March .
Norman Whatley ( 8 September 1884 -- 1 April 1965 ) was an English educationalist , headmaster of Clifton College from 1923 - 1939 , and also a historian , Fellow of Hertford College , Oxford .
Eduard Künneke ( also seen as Edward and spelled Künnecke ) ( 27 January 1885 -- 27 October 1953 ) was a German composer of operettas , operas and theatre music .
Ada Hayden ( 14 August 1884 -- 12 August 1950 ) was an American botanist , educator , and preservationist .
Sol Liptzin ( 1901 -- 15 November 1995 ) was a scholar , author , and educator in Yiddish and German literature .
Andrej Bicenko ( October 17 , 1886 -- 1985 ) also spelled Andrei Bicenko , Andrey Bitsenko ( Russian Cyrillic:Андрей Васильевич Биценко ) was a Russian fresco painter .
Captain John Dibbs , ( 1790 - -1872 ) was a master mariner prominent during 1822 - -1835 in the seas around the colony of New South Wales , New Zealand and the Society Islands ( now Tahiti ) .
Přemek I , Duke of Opava ' ( or Przemko I ) ( Czech : Přemysl I. Opavský ; German : Přemysl I. von Troppau ; born : c. 1365 ; died : 28 September 1433 ) was a member of the Opava branch of the Bohemian Přemyslid dynasty .
János Bolyai ( Hungarian : ( ˈjaːnoʃ ˈboːjɒi ) ; 15 December 1802 -- 27 January 1860 ) or Johann Bolyai , was a Hungarian mathematician , one of the founders of non - Euclidean geometry -- a geometry that differs from Euclidean geometry in its definition of parallel lines .
Arthur Michael Ramsey , Baron Ramsey of Canterbury , PC ( 14 November 1904 -- 23 April 1988 ) was an English Anglican bishop and life peer .
Lionel Colin Brewill ( 1889 - -1943 ) ARIBA TD was an architect based in Nottingham .
Charles Burgess Fry , known as C. B. Fry ( 25 April 1872 -- 7 September 1956 ) , was an English polymath ; an outstanding sportsman , politician , diplomat , academic , teacher , writer , editor and publisher , who is best remembered for his career as a cricketer .
Barnim VI , Duke of Pomerania ( c. 1365 -- 22 September 1405 in Pütnitz , near Ribnitz - Damgarten ) was duke of Pomerania - Wolgast from 1394 to 1405 .
John Flete ( ca . 1398 -- 1466 ) was an English monk and ecclesiastical historian who documented the history and abbots of Westminster Abbey .
Maria Luisa Zuloaga de Tovar ( 1902 - -1992 ) was a Venezuelan ceramicist .
Cecil Stanley Harrison , CMG OBE ( 17 November 1902 -- 14 April 1962 ) was Bailiff of Jersey from 1961 to 1962 .
Ricardo Mórtola Di Puglia ( c. 1950 -- 22 April 2014 ) was an Ecuadorian architect and businessman .
Carroll Vincent Newsom ( 1904 - 1990 ) was an American educator who served as the eleventh NYU President and President of Prentice Hall .
Don Whiteside ( 1931 - 1993 ) was a sociologist , native author , Canadian civil servant , and founder and president of the Civil Liberties Association , National Capital Region .
Sir Adolphus Oughton , 1st Baronet ( c. 1685 -- 4 September 1736 ) , was a British politician .
Melvin E. Sherwin ( 1881 - 1924 ) was a founding member of FarmHouse fraternity at the University of Missouri , and was later the head of the soils department at what is now called North Carolina State University from 1910 until his death in 1924 at the age of 42 .
Rabbi Simcha Elberg ( known as עלבערג שמחה in Hebrew ) ( 1915 - -1995 ) was a renowned Talmudic scholar and the chairman on the executive board of the Union of Orthodox Rabbis for 25 years .
Paul Parin ( 20 September 1916 -- 18 May 2009 ) was a Swiss psychoanalyst , author and ethnologist .
Vlatko Konjevod ( 1923 in Sarajevo -- December 2005 ) was a Yugoslav footballer and football manager .
Mabel Cawthra Adamson ( 1871 - -1943 ) was a Canadian painter and decorator , active in the Arts and Crafts movement in Toronto .
Marc - Edmond Dominé ( 21 June 1848 - 28 June 1921 ) was a French Army officer who served in the Franco - Prussian War , the Sino - French War , and in the various territories of the French colonial empire .
Sarabjit Singh ( also spelled Sarabjeet Singh ; Punjabi : ਸਰਬਜੀਤ ਸਿੰਘ ; 1963 or 1964 -- 2 May 2013 ) ( alleged to be Manjit Singh by Pakistan ) was an Indian national convicted of terrorism and spying by a Pakistani court .
Johan Robert Selfelt ( 22 May 1903 -- 24 August 1987 ) was a Swedish horse rider .
George Herbert Carpenter ( 1865 - -1939 ) was a British naturalist and entomologist , born in the Peckham district of southeast London in 1865 , and died in Belfast on 22 January 1939 .
Jere Abbott ( 1897 - -1982 ) , was the first associate director of the Museum of Modern Art in New York .
The Hon . Gregor McGregor ( 18 October 1848 -- 13 August 1914 ) was an influential Australian politician and trade union leader of the late nineteenth and early twentieth century .
William Wellesley - Pole , 3rd Earl of Mornington GCH PC PC ( Ire ) ( 20 May 1763 -- 22 February 1845 ) , known as Lord Maryborough between 1821 and 1842 , was an Anglo - Irish politician and an elder brother of the Duke of Wellington .
Michael James Casey ( 19 February 1918 -- 31 March 1944 ) , known as `` Mike '' , was a British Blenheim bomber pilot of Irish descent who was taken prisoner during the Second World War .
Geoffrey Phibbs ( Norfolk,1900-Dublin , 1956 ) was an Irish poet ; he took his mother 's name and called himself Geoffrey Taylor , after about 1930 .
Jimmy Tansey ( 29 January 1929 -- 7 July 2012 ) was an English professional footballer who played for Everton and Crewe Alexandra .
Helmut Zacharias ( 27 January 1920 -- 28 February 2002 ) was a German violinist and composer who created over 400 works and sold 14 million records .
Ernst Rudolf Huber ( 8 June 1903 -- 28 October 1990 ) was a German jurist , noted as a constitutional historian and for his attempts to provide a legal underpinning for the Nazi regime .
Saint Goar of Aquitaine ( c. 585 -- 6 July 649 ) was a priest and hermit of the seventh century .
Justice T. V. R. Tatachari BSc , B.L. ( 16 October 1916 -- 1 June 2001 ) was Chief Justice of Delhi High Court .
Umarali Quvvatov ( Tajik : Умаралӣ Қувватов ; 21 November 1968 -- 5 March 2015 ) was a Tajikistani businessman and politician .
Gery Scott ( 5 October 1923 -- 14 December 2005 ) was a jazz and cabaret entertainer and teacher , whose performing career spanned 26 countries and over 60 years .
Sir Edward Charles Stirling CMG , MA , MD , DSc , FRS , FRCS ( 8 September 1848 -- 20 March 1919 ) was an Australian anthropologist and the first professor of physiology at the University of Adelaide .
General Douglas Hamilton ( 8 April 1818 -- 20 January 1892 ) was a British Indian Army officer , gazetted to the 21st Regiment of the Madras Native Infantry from 1837 to 1871 .
Paul Van Asbroeck ( 1 May 1874 -- 1959 ) was a Belgian sports shooter who competed in the early 20th century in rifle and pistol shooting .
Walter Richard Cassels ( 4 September 1826 in London -- 10 June 1907 ) is the speculated author of the anonymous work Supernatural Religion .
Jacinto Caamaño Moraleja ( 1759 - 1825 ? ) was the leader of the last great Spanish exploration of Alaska ( then Russian America ) and the Coast of British Columbia .
Teresia Constantia Phillips or Con Phillips ( 2 January 1709 -- 2 February 1765 ) was a British courtesan and bigamist who published a scandalous autobiography .
Francis Raven ( April 26 , 1914 - December 1983 ) was an American cryptologist and an early employee of the National Security Agency .
Francis Robert Bonham ( 6 September 1785 -- 26 April 1863 ) was a British party agent and politician .
Stefan Ossowiecki ( 1877 - -1944 ) was a Polish engineer who was , during his lifetime , promoted as one of Europe 's best - known psychics .
Lupu Coci , known as Vasile Lupu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( vaˈsile ˈlupu ) ; 1595 - -1661 ) was the Voivode of Moldavia between 1634 and 1653 .
John Heaviside Clark ( c.1771 - -1836 ) was a Scottish aquatint engraver and painter of seascapes and landscapes .
Babë Dud Karbunara ( 1842 - -1917 ) , born Jorgji Karbunara was an Albanian teacher and politician .
Bogumil Vošnjak , also known as Bogomil Vošnjak ( 9 September 1882 -- 18 June 1955 ) was a Slovene and Yugoslav jurist , politician , diplomat , author and legal historian .
Lissy Schmidt ( ca . 1959 -- 3 April 1994 ) , also known by her pseudonyms Milena Ergen and Petra Sert , was a German journalist who worked for the Agence France Presse , Frankfurter Rundschau ( Frankfurt ) , and Der Tagesspiegel ( Berlin ) .
Edward Greswell ( 1797 - -1869 ) was an English churchman and academic , known as a chronologist .
John Douglas , 7th Marquess of Queensberry ( 1779 -- 19 December 1856 ) , styled Lord John Douglas from May to December 1837 , was a Scottish Whig politician .
Peter Gunnarsson Rambo ( 1612 - -1698 ) was a Swedish immigrant to New Sweden who lived as a farmer and served as a justice on the Governor 's Council .
Christian Albert , Burgrave and Count of Dohna ( also known as Christoph Albert , 10 December 1621 in Küstrin & nash ; 14 December 1677 in Gartz ) was a German nobleman .
Michel Martin Drolling ( 7 March 1789 -- 9 January 1851 ) was a neoclassic French painter , painter of history and portraitist .
Choe Bu ( 1454 - -1504 ) was a Korean official during the early Joseon Dynasty ( 1392 - -1910 ) .
Brian Desmond Hurst ( 12 February 1895 -- 26 September 1986 ) was a Belfast - born film director .
Zheng Zhong ( 鄭眾 ) , courtesy name Jichan ( 季產 ) ( died 107 ) , was the first Han Dynasty eunuch with true power in government , thanks to the trust that Emperor He had in him for his contributions in overthrowing the clan of Empress Dowager Dou , particularly her autocratic brother Dou Xian .
Nedo Nadi ( 9 June 1894 -- 29 January 1940 ) was one of the best Italian fencers of all time .
Patience Collier ( 19 August 1910 -- 13 July 1987 in London ) was a British actress .
Jon Mathews ( 10 February 1932 - 1979 ) was an American scholar , physicist , author , and adventurer .
Maurice Ludmer ( 1926 - -1981 ) was a British anti - fascist activist and journalist .
Frederick IV , Duke of Saxe - Gotha - Altenburg ( Gotha , 28 November 1774 -- Gotha , 11 February 1825 ) , was the last duke of Saxe - Gotha - Altenburg .
Eugene Lee - Hamilton ( 6 January 1845 -- 9 September 1907 ) was a late Victorian English poet .
Maharani Mahtab Kaur ( b. 1782 - d. 1840 ) was the first wife of Ranjit Singh , Maharaja of Sikh Empire and daughter of Sardar Gurbakhsh Singh Kanhya .
George Morrissey ( 1 January 1883 -- 7 December 1964 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ioan Vlădea ( 24 October 1907 , Râșnov , 24 November 1976 , Timișoara ) was a Romanian engineer from IAR Brașov , who developed the compressor of plane engine IAR 80 .
Captain Dr Henry Speldewinde de Boer , CMG , MC ( 1896 - -1957 ) was a Ceylonese born British colonial doctor .
Sir Alexander Robertson Murray , KT , KStJ , KCIE , ( 29 November 1872 -- 19 March 1956 ) was a former President of the Bengal Chamber of Commerce .
Nicholas Tacitus Zegers ( c.1495 -- 25 August 1559 ) was a Flemish Franciscan biblical exegete .
Charles Christian Georgeson ( June 26 , 1851 -- 1931 ) was an agronomist , born on Langeland , Denmark .
Román Viñoly Barreto ( 8 August 1914 -- 20 August 1970 ) was a Uruguayan - Argentine film director .
Katharine Mortimer ( 1923 - -2003 ) was an American socialite .
Elof Eriksson ( 1883 - -1965 ) was a Swedish anti - Semitic political writer .
Abraham Hart ( 15 December 1810 , Philadelphia - 22 July 1885 , Long Branch , New Jersey ) was a United States publisher , a member of the noted firm of Carey and Hart .
María Elena Aldunate Bezanilla , who wrote under the name Elena Aldunate , ( March 1 , 1925 -- 2005 ) was a Chilean journalist and writer .
Teddy Lockwood ( 6 December 1872 -- 25 June 1953 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong and Collingwood during the years following the formation of the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Duckworth Benson ( 1857 - -1926 ) , known as T. D. Benson , was a British socialist activist .
Jack Hixon ( 1921 -- 20 December 2009 ) was an English football talent scout .
Tim Guest ( 16 July 1975 -- 31 July 2009 ) ( also known as Yogesh and Errol Mysterio ) was an English author and journalist .
Emil Bobu ( 22 February 1927 -- 12 July 2014 ) was a Romanian Communist activist and politician , who served as Interior Minister from 1973 to 1975 and as Labor Minister from 1979 to 1981 .
Steve Hanson ( 7 August 1961 -- 4 November 2015 ) was a professional rugby league player in the New South Wales Rugby League ( NSWRL ) competition .
Benjamin W. Arnett ( 1838 - -1906 ) was an African - American educator , minister , bishop and elected official .
György Lahner ( Hungarian : Lahner György , Láhner György , German : Georg Lahner ; 6 October 1795 , Necpál ( Slovak : Necpaly ) - 6 October 1849 , Arad ) was a honvéd general in the Hungarian Army .
Fazle Lohani ( Bengali : ফজেল লোহানী ; 12 March 1929 -- 30 October 1985 ) was a Bangladeshi journalist , television host , songwriter and film producer .
H. Cooper Cliffe ( 19 July 1862 - 1 May 1939 ) was a British stage and screen actor a member of a distinguished family of English actors , his father was Clifford Cooper , mother Agnes Kemble , and his brother was Frank Kemble Cooper .
Ishak Pasha ( Turkish : İshak Paşa ; fl . 1469 - -died 1497 ) was an Ottoman general , statesman , and later Grand Vizier .
Harold Marshall Sylvester Richards Sr . ( 1894 - -1985 ) , commonly known as H. M. S. Richards , was a well - known Seventh - day Adventist evangelist and author .
Paidi Lakshmayya BA , B.L. ( Telugu : పైడి లక్ష్మయ్య ) ( 26 April 1904 -- 28 April 1987 ) was Indian Parliamentarian , actor , writer and administrator .
Saint Matthias of Jerusalem ( died 120 AD ) was a 2nd century Christian saint and a Bishop of Jerusalem , who 's episcapcy was about 113 - 120AD .
Robert Welles , 8th Baron Willoughby de Eresby and Baron Welles ( died 19 March 1470 ) , was the son of Richard Welles , 7th Baron Welles , and Joan Willoughby , 7th Baroness Willoughby de Eresby .
David Victor Emmanuel ( 10 February 1963 -- 15 March 2011 ) , better known as Smiley Culture , was a British reggae singer and DJ known for his ' fast chat ' style .
Sir James Douglas Cooke , FRCS ( 1879 -- 13 July 1949 ) was a Conservative politician from England .
Thomas Simpson Cooke ( `` Tom Cooke '' ) ( July 1782 -- 26 February 1848 ) was an Irish composer , conductor , singer , theatre musician and music director -- an influential figure in early 19th - century opera in London .
Sir John Sulman ( 29 August 1849 -- 18 August 1934 ) was an Australian architect .
Jean - Baptiste Barsalou ( 9 September 1706 -- 18 March 1776 ) was from a business family in Montreal , his father having been a master tanner with his own business in that location .
Adam Beckett ( born 1950 , Los Angeles , California , died 1979 , Val Verde , California ) was an animator , special effects artist and teacher , most notable for his work on Star Wars .
Augustine Francis Hewit ( Fairfield , Connecticut , U.S.A. , 27 November 1820 -- New York , 3 July 1897 ) was an American Redemptorist priest , and second Superior General of the Paulist Fathers .
Donal Collins was found dead in his home in County Wexford on the evening of 9 April 2010 .
Anders Peter Nielsen ( 25 May 1867 -- 16 April 1950 ) was a Danish shooter who competed in the late 19th century and early 20th century in rifle shooting .
James Clarke Hook RA ( 21 November 1819 -- 14 April 1907 ) was an English painter and etcher of marine , genre and historical scenes , and landscapes .
Merv Storey ( 20 November 1913 -- 13 July 1977 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Pierre - Paul Saunier ( 1751 - -1818 ) was a gardener who worked first at Montbard in Eastern France , and then at the Jardin du Roi in Paris where he was a protégé of head gardener André Thouin ( 1746 - -1824 ) .
Bruce Bursford ( 29 April 1958 - 9 February 2000 ) was a British sportsman who broke the record for the fastest speed on a bicycle on a treadmill at 334.6 km / h in 1996 .
Alexander Alexeyevich Borisov ( Russian : Александр Алексеевич Борисов , 14 November ( O.S. 2 November ) 1866 -- 17 August 1934 ) was a Russian painter notable for his Arctic landscapes .
Petpet Park was a virtual pet website launched by Nickelodeon Kids & Family Virtual Worlds Group ( formerly Neopets ) in October 2008 .
The Graphics Interchange Format ( better known by its acronym GIF /ˈdʒɪf/ JIF or /ˈɡɪf/ GHIF ) is a bitmap image format that was introduced by CompuServe in 1987 and has since come into widespread usage on the World Wide Web due to its wide support and portability .
ESPN MLS GameNight is a video game of the sports genre released in 2000 by Konami and Saffire Corporation .

Extase is a computer game that was created in 1990 by Cryo Interactive , and published by Virgin Games .

Grid MP is a commercial distributed computing software package developed and sold by Univa ( formerly known as United Devices ) , a privately held company based primarily in Austin , Texas .

Benjamin de Rothschild studied at the Swiss Institut Florimont and holds a BA in Business Management from Pepperdine University .
Van Ellis Huff ( 1894 -- 1987 ) was a University of Florida trained engineer who popularized residential use of a combination jalousie window .
Seweryn Bialer ( born November 3 , 1926 ) is an emeritus professor of political science at Columbia University and an expert on the Communist parties of the Soviet Union and Poland .
Leonard Greene graduated in 1938 from the City College of New York with a B.S. in Chemistry , and went on to receive a M.S. in aeronautical engineering .
Between 1926 and 1932 , Horia Sima was a student at the Faculty of Letters and Philosophy of the University of Bucharest .
Clay Dreslough is the creator of the Baseball Mogul and Football Mogul computer sports games , and is the co - founder and President of Sports Mogul , Inc. He was born in Boston , Massachusetts ( USA ) and graduated from Wesleyan University .
Athene Seyler was President of the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art ( RADA ) from 1950 , and a member of the Theatrical Ladies Guild .
John Edward King ( 10 July 1858 -- 21 March 1939 ) was an author , Fellow and Tutor of Lincoln College , Oxford , High Master of Manchester Grammar School , Headmaster of Bedford School , and Headmaster of Clifton College .
David Kassan received his B.F.A. in 1999 from the College of Visual and Performing Arts at Syracuse University , Syracuse , NY .
Matthew Price was educated at The Haberdashers ' Aske 's Boys ' School , a day independent school in Elstree in Hertfordshire , followed by St Catharine 's College at the University of Cambridge , gaining a First Class degree in Geography .

Dele Young attended George Mason University where he earned a degree in Economics .
At Northwestern University , Larry Brody majored in English and wrote dozens of short stories , poetry and essays .
After receiving a Bachelor of Arts degree from Uppsala University , Rickard Sandler became a teacher at a folk high school in Kramfors ( where his father was headmaster ) and another in Brunnsvik .
Nari Ward received a BA from Hunter College , CUNY in 1991 and a MFA from Brooklyn College , CUNY in 1992 .
Daniel Thürer ( born 6 June 1945 in St. Gallen ) is a Swiss jurist and professor emeritus of international , comparative constitutional and European law at the University of Zurich .
Born in 1961 in Paris , Hugues Absil studied in the École nationale supérieure des Beaux - Arts .
Clements Ripley attended the Taft School and graduated from Yale University in 1916 .

Henry Coddington ( 1798/9 , Oldbridge , County Meath -- 3 March 1845 , Rome ) was an English natural philosopher , fellow and tutor of Trinity College , Cambridge and Church of England clergyman .

Radim Palouš ( 6 November 1924 -- 10 September 2015 ) was a Czech dissident , philosopher , educator , and former spokesman for Charter 77 , and from 1990 to 1994 , was the rector of Charles University in Prague .
Ben Askren ( born July 18 , 1984 ) is an American former amateur wrestler for the University of Missouri and U.S. Olympic team .
Uzi Even ( Hebrew : עוזי אבן‎ , born 18 October 1940 ) is an Israeli professor emeritus of physical chemistry at Tel Aviv University and a former politician well known for being the first openly gay member of the Knesset .
Claudia Goldin ( born May 14 , 1946 ) is an American economist and Henry Lee Professor of Economics at Harvard University .

Viv Fisher ( born 1952 ) is an ex - BBC audio engineer and multivocalist who performed all parts of the brass band used in the title sequence of the BBC 's 1985 TV series , Blott on the Landscape .
Charles J. Fillmore ( August 9 , 1929 -- February 13 , 2014 ) was an American linguist and Professor of Linguistics at the University of California , Berkeley .
Janet Adelman ( January 28 , 1941 -- April 6 , 2010 ) was a Shakespearean scholar , a literary critic , and professor of English at the University of California , Berkeley .
Craig Hogan is a Professor of Astronomy and Physics at the University of Chicago and he is the director of the Fermilab Center for Particle Astrophysics .

Theda Skocpol ( born May 4 , 1947 ) is an American sociologist and political scientist at Harvard University .

Bruce W. Warren is a professor of archeology at Brigham Young University .

Ameerah Haq is a Bangladeshi technocrat who served as United Nations Under - Secretary - General for the Department of Field Support , the highest - ranking Bangladeshi official at the United Nations , from April 2012 until her resignation in July 2014 .
Tim Donovan is the political editor for the BBC 's regional news service for London , BBC London News .
Alberto Gainza Paz ( March 16 , 1899 - December 26 , 1977 ) was an Argentine journalist and political activist who served as editor of the newspaper La Prensa .
Robin Burgess is a Professor of Economics , Founder and Director of the International Growth Centre , and Co - Director of the Economic Organisation and Public Policy Programme at the London School of Economics and Political Science .
John Suppe is an American geologist who is Professor of Geology at National Taiwan University and Princeton University .
Stephen F. Jones ( born c. 1952 ) is an American expert on post - Communist societies in the former Soviet Union and Eastern Europe who currently serves as Chair of Russian and Eurasian Studies at Mount Holyoke College , South Hadley , Massachusetts .
David Hackett Fischer ( born December 2 , 1935 ) is University Professor and Earl Warren Professor of History at Brandeis University .
Sally Haslanger is the Ford Professor of Philosophy in the Department of Linguistics and Philosophy at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and holds the 2015 Spinoza Chair of Philosophy at the University of Amsterdam .
P. Dee Boersma is a conservation biologist and professor at the University of Washington , where she is Wadsworth Endowed Chair in Conservation Science .
Zabihollah Safa ( Persian : ذبیح‌اللّه صفا‎‎ ) ( May 7 , 1911 in Shahmirzad , Iran -- April 29 , 1999 in Lübeck , Germany ) was a scholar and professor Emeritus of Iranian Studies at the University of Tehran .

Kate Fenton ( born 14 October 1954 ) is an English novelist and former BBC radio producer .
Isidro Fabela received his Law degree from the National School of Law at the National Autonomous University of Mexico ( Spanish : Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México ) ( UNAM ) in 1908 .
John Bensko is an award - winning American poet who teaches in the MFA program at the University of Memphis , along with his wife , the fiction writer Cary Holladay .

Kevin Marsh ( born 14 November 1954 ) is the Editor of the BBC College of Journalism .
Mauno Jokipii ( 21 August 1924 -- 2 January 2007 ) was a Finnish professor at the University of Jyväskylä in history specializing in World War II . He was a thorough investigator and a prolific author .
Karl Taylor Compton ( September 14 , 1887 -- June 22 , 1954 ) was a prominent American physicist and president of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( MIT ) from 1930 to 1948 .
Hjalte Rasmussen ( December 18 , 1940 - August 9 , 2012 ) was Professor of European Union Law at the University of Copenhagen .
Christos Hatzis ( Greek : Χρήστος Χατζής ; born 1953 ) is a Greek Canadian composer currently a professor at the Faculty of Music , University of Toronto .

Teófilo Herrera Suárez ( born 24 February 1924 ) is a Mexican mycologist known for his contributions to the Mexican mycological flora and an Emeritus Professor at the National Autonomous University of Mexico ( UNAM ) where he worked for over 50 years .
Heribert Adam ( born 1936 ) is professor emeritus of political sociology at Simon Fraser University , specializing in human rights , comparative racisms , peace studies , Southern Africa , and ethnic conflict .
Renée A. Blake is a Caribbean - American linguistics professor at New York University .
Wolfram Hoepfner ( born 16 March 1937 in Breslau ) is a German classicist , archaeologist , architectural historian , and Professor of Ancient Architectural History , at the Free University of Berlin .
Charles Cadwell , was a professor at the Case School of Applied Science ( now Case Western Reserve University ) , in Cleveland , Ohio .

Alfredo Lopes Cabral ( born 1946 ) is a Guinea - Bissauan diplomat and United Nations official .

Nathan A. Scott , Jr. ( 24 April 1925 -- December 2006 ) was an American scholar who helped establish the modern field of theology and literature and who helped found the well - known Ph.D. program in that field at the University of Chicago .
Dave Pascal ( 1918 , Manhattan-3 March 2003 , New York ) was an American cartoonist whose work has appeared in The New Yorker and elsewhere .

Peter Alliss ( born 28 February 1931 ) is a former English professional golfer , and is a BBC television presenter and commentator , author and golf course designer .

Waiwera is a locality situated in the north of the Auckland Region in New Zealand .
Double Eagle II , piloted by Ben Abruzzo , Maxie Anderson , and Larry Newman , became the first balloon to cross the Atlantic Ocean when it landed 17 August 1978 in Miserey near Paris , 137 hours 6 minutes after leaving Presque Isle , Maine .

General Francis Richard Dannatt , Baron Dannatt GCB , CBE , MC , DL ( born 23 December 1950 ) is a retired British Army officer and the incumbent Constable of the Tower of London .

The Royal Fusiliers ( City of London Regiment ) was a line infantry regiment of the British Army in continuous existence for 283 years .

The Portage Diversion consists of two separate gates which divert some of the flow of water in the Assiniboine River to a 29 km long diversion channel that empties into Lake Manitoba near Delta Beach .

Aberfoyle River rises on the slopes of the Great Dividing Range , at Llangothlin , north of Guyra , and flows generally south southeast , east southeast , northeast , and east northeast , joined by three minor tributaries towards its confluence with the Guy Fawkes River , below Chaelundi Mountain , within Guy Fawkes River National Park .
The Verde River ( Yavapai : Haka'he : la ) is a major tributary of the Salt River in the U.S. state of Arizona .

The Thouet ( pronounced : ( tu.e ) ) is a tributary river of the Loire in the Poitou - Charentes and Pays de la Loire régions of France .

The Orlovka River ( Russian : Орловка ) is a river in Tomsk Oblast with its origins in Krasnoyarsk Krai in Russia , a right tributary of the Ket River ( Ob basin ) .
J. B. Lippincott & Co. was an American publishing house founded in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania in 1836 by Joshua Ballinger Lippincott .
The Hessian matrix was developed in the 19th century by the German mathematician Ludwig Otto Hesse and later named after him .
Aristarchus ' inequality ( after the Greek astronomer and mathematician Aristarchus of Samos ; c. 310 -- c. 230 BCE ) is a law of trigonometry which states that if α and β are acute angles ( i.e. between 0 and a right angle ) and β < α then \frac(\sin\alpha)(\sin\beta ) < \frac(\alpha)(\beta ) < \frac(\tan\alpha)(\tan\beta ) .
The Fraser spiral illusion is an optical illusion that was first described by the British psychologist Sir James Fraser ( 1863 -- 1936 ) in 1908 .
In algebraic geometry , the Stein factorization , introduced by Karl Stein ( 1956 ) for the case of complex spaces , states that a proper morphism can be factorized as a composition of a finite mapping and a proper morphism with connected fibers .
Namaland was a bantustan in South West Africa ( present - day Namibia ) , intended by the apartheid government to be a self - governing homeland for the Nama people .

In mathematics , the Kampé de Fériet function is a two - variable generalization of the generalized hypergeometric series , introduced by Joseph Kampé de Fériet .
Shamir 's Secret Sharing is an algorithm in cryptography created by Adi Shamir .
In mathematics , Hilbert 's second problem was posed by David Hilbert in 1900 as one of his 23 problems .

In mathematics , the Cauchy principal value , named after Augustin Louis Cauchy , is a method for assigning values to certain improper integrals which would otherwise be undefined .

Silvester ( also spelled sylvester , szilveszter , or sylwester ) is the day of the Feast of Pope Sylvester I , a saint who served as Pope of the Catholic Church from 314 to 335 and oversaw both the First Council of Nicaea and Roman Emperor Constantine I 's conversion to Christianity .

Murray Ward was an Australian rules footballer with the Claremont Football Club during the 1950s and 60 's .

Cameron Skelton ( born 8 March 1995 in Auckland , New Zealand ) , is a professional rugby union player who plays for the Waikato Chiefs in the Super 15 competition .

Ignacy Krasicki was the leading literary representative of the Polish Enlightenment -- a prose writer and poet highly esteemed by his contemporaries , who admired his works for their wit , imagination and fluid style .

Emily Wright ( born July 1 , 1980 ) is an American songwriter , producer and engineer currently based in Nashville .

Paul the Persian or Paulus Persa was a 6th - century East Syrian theologian and philosopher who worked at the court of the Sassanid king Khosrau I. He wrote several treatises and commentaries on Aristotle , which had some influence on medieval Islamic philosophy .

Ahsan Mubarak ( Urdu : احسن مبارک ; SI , DSc ) , is a Pakistani geophysicist and nuclear seismologist who is renowned for his pioneering research on earthquake sciences , and seismic activities in Pakistan .
Hubert Best ( born 1952 ) was an English cathedral organist , who served in St. Philip 's Cathedral , Birmingham .

William 's mbuna ( Maylandia greshakei ) , also known as ice blue zebra or the Pseudotropheus ice blue among the aquarium enthusiasts , is a species of cichlid fish endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only found at Makokola in the southeastern arm of the lake .

Phocine distemper virus ( PDV ) is a paramyxovirus of the genus Morbillivirus that is pathogenic for pinniped species , particularly seals .
The Chapman 's antshrike ( Thamnophilus zarumae ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .

Phytosaurs are generally regarded as the most basal group of Crurotarsi , a clade of archosaurs that includes crocodilians and their extinct relatives .

Eremascus is the sole genus in the fungal family Eremascaceae .
Chalcolampra is a genus of leaf beetles contained in the family Chrysomelidae .
Mikadotrochus is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pleurotomariidae , the slit snails .
The Chinese bahaba ( Bahaba taipingensis ) is a species of marine fish in the Sciaenidae family .
The Asian palm civet ( Paradoxurus hermaphroditus ) , also called toddy cat , is a small member of the family Viverridae native to South and Southeast Asia .
The Spotfin flounder ( Cyclopsetta fimbriata ) is a species of large - tooth flounder native to the western Atlantic Ocean .
Tapinanthus is a genus of mistletoe in family Loranthaceae .
Fonticula , Nuclearia , and Fungi have been united into the Nucletmycea , which is sister to the Holozoa .
Tascina is a genus of moths within the Castniidae family .

The Mindanao treeshrew ( Urogale everetti ) , also called the Philippine tree shrew , is a species of treeshrew endemic to the Mindanao region in the Philippines .

Rhizophagoides kojimai is a species of beetle in the family Monotomidae , the only species in the genus Rhizophagoides .
Thaumatodon is a genus of minute air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Endodontidae .
Chaetocerotophycidae is a grouping of Coscinodiscophyceae , previously known as `` Centrales '' .
Handkea utriformis , synonymous with Lycoperdon utriforme , Lycoperdon caelatum or Calvatia utriformis , is a species of the Lycoperdaceae family of puffballs .
Otomyini is an Old World tribe of muroid rodents in the subfamily Murinae .
Anthias are members of the family Serranidae ( basses , basslets , groupers ) and make up the subfamily Anthiinae .
The genus Myosurus , or mousetail , belongs to the buttercup family ( Ranunculaceae ) .
Pseudophloeus fuscicornis is a species of beetle in the family Laemophloeidae , the only species in the genus Pseudophloeus .
Paraperrinitinae is one of two subfamilies of the Perrinitidae superfamily .
Thomas 's giant deer mouse ( Megadontomys thomasi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Babycurus is a genus of scorpions belonging to the family Buthidae .
Matschie 's dwarf gecko ( Lygodactylus conradti ) is a species of gecko native to eastern Tanzania , eastern Kenya , and western Cameroon .
The Nyika rock rat ( Aethomys nyikae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Angola , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Malawi , and Zambia .
The Cocos finch or Cocos Island finch ( Pinaroloxias inornata ) is the only one of Darwin 's finches not native to the Galápagos Islands , and the only member of the genus Pinaroloxias .
Grace 's warbler ( Setophaga graciae ) is a small New World warbler that specializes in pine woods .
Geoffroy 's spider monkey ( Ateles geoffroyi ) , also known as the black - handed spider monkey , is a species of spider monkey , a type of New World monkey , from Central America , parts of Mexico and possibly a small portion of Colombia .

Notoplatynus darlingtoni is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Notoplatynus .

Triatoma is a genus of assassin bug in the subfamily Triatominae ( kissing bugs ) .
Acanalonia is a genus of planthopper in the fulgorid family Acanaloniidae .

The Japanese angelshark ( Squatina japonica ) is a species of angel shark , family Squatinidae , found in the northwestern Pacific Ocean off China , Japan , and Korea .

Crassodontidanus is an extinct genus of sharks and the sole member of the family Crassonotidae , in the order Hexanchiformes .
Alnus oblongifolia ( Arizona Alder ) is a large alder , birch - family tree up to 72 feet ( 22 m ) , from the southwestern United States and northern Sonora , Mexico .

Lina Kačiušytė ( born January 1 , 1963 in Vilnius , Lithuanian SSR ) is a Lithuanian swimmer who competed for the Soviet Union , winner of a gold medal in 200 m breaststroke with the Olympic record time of 2:29:54 at the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Chen Zuo ( born 1982 - 01 - 19 in Beijing ) is a Chinese swimmer , who competed for Team China at the 2004 Summer Olympics , the 2008 Summer Olympics and was an unused substitute in the men 's relay at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
János Adorján ( October 30 , 1938 in Budapest -- December 15 , 1995 in Budapest ) is a former Hungarian handball player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Eduard Meijer ( 25 February 1878 , Amsterdam -- 20 March 1929 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch freestyle swimmer and water polo player who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics and 1908 Summer Olympics .
Md Mizanur Rahman ( Bengali : মোঃ মিজানুর রহমান ) ( born 15 September 1978 ) is a Bangladeshi kabaddi player who was part of the team that won the bronze medal at the 2006 Asian Games .
Roberto Heras Hernández ( born 1 February 1974 ) is a Spanish former professional road bicycle racer who won the Vuelta a España ( Tour of Spain ) a record - tying three times .
Frans G. Hu Kon ( born 1917 , date of death unknown ) was an Indonesian football defender who played for the Dutch East Indies in the 1938 FIFA World Cup .
Wael Al - Aydy ( Arabic : وائل العايدي‎ ) ( born December 8 , 1971 ) is an Egyptian indoor volleyball player , who played with the Egypt national team at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
An Yulong ( born 23 July 1978 ) is a Chinese short track speed skater , who won medals in the 500 m and 5000 m relay at the 1998 Winter Olympics .
Joseph Mauclair ( Clichy , 9 March 1906 -- Créteil , 5 February 1990 ) was a French professional road bicycle racer from 1927 to 1938 , who won the 17th stage in the 1928 Tour de France .
Heidi Voelker ( born 17 June 1968 in Pittsfield , Massachusetts ) is an American former alpine skier who competed in the 1988 Winter Olympics , 1992 Winter Olympics , and 1994 Winter Olympics .
Ketil Hodne ( born 12 April 1947 ) was a Norwegian amateur boxer who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Fabio Casartelli ( 16 August 1970 -- 18 July 1995 ) was an Italian cyclist and an Olympic gold medalist who died in a crash on the descent of the Col de Portet d'Aspet , France , during the 15th stage of the 1995 Tour de France .
Franjo Arapović ( born June 2 , 1965 ) is a former Croatian basketball center - 7 ft 0.5 in ( 2.15 m ) tall - who won the silver medal with the Croatia national basketball team at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .
Sergey Ulegin ( born October 8 , 1977 in Engels ) is a Russian canoer who has been competing since 2001 He won a silver in the men 's C-2 500 m event at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing .
Jacques Bohée ( 16 August 1929 -- 17 March 1977 ) was a French football midfielder who was a member of the French squad at the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Soe Min Thu represented Myanmar at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing , where he competed for the men 's 5,000 metres .
Elshod Rasulov ( born March 7 , 1986 in Kokand , Uzbek SSR ) is an amateur boxer from Uzbekistan , who won gold at the 2006 Asian Games and at the 2010 Asian Games and silver at 2009 World Amateur Boxing Championships .
Adolfo Mancuso is an Argentine swimmer who competed at the 1948 Summer Olympics in the 1500 m freestyle .
Eric Verdonk ( born 28 May 1959 in Taihape , New Zealand of Dutch descent ) is a former New Zealand rower who won an Olympic bronze medal at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul in the single sculls .
Aurelio González Puente ( born July 26 , 1940 in Valle de Villaverde ) is a Spanish former road bicycle racer who won the Mountains classification in the 1968 Tour de France and the Mountains classification in the 1967 Giro d'Italia .
François Vergucht was a Belgian rower who won a Silver medal in eights at the 1908 Summer Olympics .
Thomas Schertwitis ( born 2 September 1972 in Alma - Ata , Kazakh SSR ) is a German water polo player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics and in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Neville Frances Bult ( 27 June 1913 -- 30 June 2008 ) , later known by her married name Frances Vorrath , was an Australian freestyle swimmer who competed in the 1932 Summer Olympics .
Anders Bergman ( born August 6 , 1963 ) is an ice hockey goaltender who was a member of the Swedish national team at the 1987 Canada Cup and 1988 Winter Olympics , but did not play in either event .
Bjarne Jeppesen ( born August 19 , 1954 ) is a former Danish handball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Robert Zurbriggen ( 16 March 1917 -- 21 April 1952 ) was a Swiss cross - country skier and biathlete who competed in the 1948 Winter Olympics .
Edvard Möller ( Edvard Carl Möller February 13 , 1888 -- June 23 , 1920 ) was a Swedish athlete who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Oscar Frederick Hedlund ( born in Woburn , Massachusetts August 26 , 1887 and died in Cambridge , Massachusetts December 8 , 1971 ) was an American track and field athlete who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Marius Mora ( born 23 June 1921 ) is a former French cross - country skier who competed in the 1948 Winter Olympics .
Carlo Gerosa ( born 30 November 1964 ) is an Italian former alpine skier who competed in the 1988 Winter Olympics and 1992 Winter Olympics .
Jean - Jacques Boussemart ( born 22 April 1963 ) is a French former sprinter who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Eugen Corrodi ( 2 July 1922 -- 7 September 1975 ) is a Swiss football goalkeeper who played for Switzerland in the 1950 FIFA World Cup .
Tony Ramoin ( born December 23 , 1988 in Cannes ) is a French snowboarder and Olympic athlete who won a bronze medal in snowboard cross at the 2010 Winter Olympics .
José Vicente ( born 3 February 1922 ) is a Puerto Rican former pole vaulter who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics and in the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Zsigmond Nagy ( 27 July 1937 in Csengőd -- 1 March 2010 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian shot putter who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Jason Begg - Smith ( born 21 November 1980 in Vancouver , British Columbia , Canada ) is an Australian - Canadian freestyle skier , who competed in the 2006 Winter Olympics .
Alex Righetti ( born August 14 , 1977 ) is a basketball player , who won the silver medal with the Italian men 's national team at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Selina Follas ( born 21 July 1976 in Adelaide ) was a softball player from Australia , who won a bronze medal at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Renan Dal Zotto known as Renan ( born July 19 , 1960 ) is a Brazilian former volleyball player who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics , in the 1984 Summer Olympics , and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Rodolfo Mijares ( born 17 July 1938 in Delicias , Chihuahua ) is a Mexican former track and field athlete who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics .

O Gosto da Criação is the seventeenth album by Brazilian solo artist Zé Ramalho .

`` This Old Town '' is a song collaboration by English musicians Paul Weller ( formerly of The Jam ) and Graham Coxon ( of Blur fame ) .
The Great Fatsby is the second album by American rock guitarist , singer and songwriter Leslie West .
`` Ay Chico ( Lengua Afuera ) '' ( English : `` Hey Boy ( Tongue Out ) '' ) is the second single from the album El Mariel by American rap artist Pitbull .
Van Lear Rose is an album by Loretta Lynn , released in 2004 and produced by Jack White of the rock band the White Stripes .
Rough ' n ' Tumble is the fifteenth album by jazz saxophonist Stanley Turrentine recorded for the Blue Note label in 1966 and performed by Turrentine with Blue Mitchell , James Spaulding , Pepper Adams , McCoy Tyner , Grant Green , Bob Cranshaw , and Mickey Roker with arrangements by Duke Pearson .
`` Clothes Off ! ! '' is the fifth single from Gym Class Heroes ' third album , As Cruel as School Children .
Pet Grief is the second album by The Radio Dept . , released in 2006 .
`` Y Ahora Te Vas '' ( `` And Now You Leave '' ) is a song written and produced by singer - songwriter Marco Antonio Solís , and performed by him as the lead singer of Los Bukis .

Colour of Your Dreams is a studio album by singer - songwriter Carole King , released in March 1993 .
`` Everything Invaded '' is a song by Moonspell from the album , The Antidote .

The Conquest of You is the twelfth studio album released by the American musical group Kid Creole and the Coconuts .

Vicente Pérez Rosales ( Santiago , April 5 , 1807 -- September 6 , 1886 ) was a politician , traveller , merchant , miner and Chilean diplomat that organized the colonization by Germans and Chileans of the Llanquihue area .

Dr. Emilio Villanueva Peñaranda ( 28 November 1882 , in La Paz , Bolivia -- 14 Mai 1970 , in La Paz , Bolivia ) was a revolutionary Bolivian architect .
Marcel - Henri Jaspar ( Schaerbeek , 23 June 1901 - Ixelles , 14 May 1982 ) , was a Belgian lawyer and Liberal politician .
Alfonso Carlos Comín Ros ( 1933 in Zaragoza -- 23 July 1980 in Barcelona ) was a Spanish industrial engineer , politician , and polygraph who carried out his work in Catalonia .
Olga Desmond ( born Olga Sellin 2 November 1890 in Allenstein in East Prussia ( now Olsztyn , Poland ) ; died 2 August 1964 in Berlin ) was a German dancer and actress .
Ram Soloukhin ( Russian : Солоухин Рем Иванович , 19 November 1930 , Gus - Khrustalny ( town ) -- 6 January 1988 , Minsk ) - was a Soviet scientist , specializing in physics and mechanics fields .
Crato Bütner ( Sonneberg , 1616 - -1679 ) was a German Baroque composer who was kantor and organist in Danzig ( Polish : Gdańsk ) , first at the hospital church of St Salvator , then at Gdańsk 's oldest church , St Catherine 's .
Michel Auguste Martin Agénor Azéma de Montgravier ( 28 October 1805 , Béziers -- 14 September 1863 , Montpellier ) was a French archaeologist and soldier .
Edward F. Burns , Jr. ( born January 28 , 1931 ) is a former Republican member of the Pennsylvania House of Representatives .
Jānis Pujats ( born 14 November 1930 ) is the archbishop emeritus of Riga , Latvia , and a Cardinal .
Saint Castor of Apt ( died ca . 420 ) was a bishop of Apt , bishop during Gaul .
Gilbert Marie Michel Méranville ( 4 February 1936 ) is the Roman Catholic archbishop emeritus of the Archdiocese of Fort - de - France in Martinique .
Frank A. Cady ( December 31 , 1858 - March 30 , 1904 ) was an American lawyer , real estate dealer and politician from Marshfield , Wisconsin who served as a Republican member of the Wisconsin State Assembly , representing Wood County from 1901 - 1904 .
Abdurrahman Wahid , born Abdurrahman ad - Dakhil ( pronunciation ahb - doo - RAH - mahn wah - HEED ; 7 September 1940 -- 30 December 2009 ) , colloquially known as Gus Dur , was an Indonesian Muslim religious and political leader who served as the President of Indonesia from 1999 to 2001 .
Sabás Magaña García ( January 24 , 1921 in Morelia , Michoacán , Mexico - November 7 , 1990 ) was the bishop of the diocese of Matamoros , chosen by Pope Paul VI on December 30 , 1968 and receiving consecration in Rome on January 6 , 1969 .
Johann von Eych ( died 1464 ) was a German Roman Catholic bishop and cardinal .
Aeneas of Paris ( died December 27 , 870 ) was bishop of Paris from 858 to 870 .
Jack Cera is a member of the Ohio House of Representatives , representing the 95th district .
Robert Spendlove is an American politician and a Republican member of the Utah House of Representatives representing District 49 since January 9 , 2014 .
James Hamilton , 1st Duke of Abercorn , KG , PC ( 21 January 1811 -- 31 October 1885 ) , styled Viscount Hamilton from 1814 to 1818 and the Marquess of Abercorn from 1818 to 1868 , was a British Conservative politician and statesman who twice served as Lord Lieutenant of Ireland .
Franjo Kuharić ( 15 April 1919 -- 11 March 2002 ) was a cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Paul Henry Walsh ( August 17 , 1937 -- October 18 , 2014 ) was an American prelate of the Roman Catholic Church who served as Auxiliary bishop of the Diocese of Rockville Centre , New York from 2003 to 2012 .
Jennifer Stoddart ( born 1949 ) was the sixth Privacy Commissioner of Canada .
Zakaria Mohieddin ( 5 July 1918 -- 15 May 2012 ) ( Arabic : زكريا محيى الدين‎ , IPA : ( zækæˈɾejjæ ˈmoħj edˈdiːn ) ) was an Egyptian military officer , politician , Prime Minister of Egypt and head of the first Intelligence body in Egypt , the Egyptian General Intelligence Directorate .
Eduardo Francisco Pironio ( 3 December 1920 -- 5 February 1998 ) was an Argentine Roman Catholic cardinal who served in numerous departments of the Roman Curia in addition to his post as the Cardinal - Bishop of Sabina - Poggio .
Antonín Zápotocký ( 19 December 1884 -- 13 November 1957 ) was communist Prime Minister of Czechoslovakia from 1948 to 1953 and President of Czechoslovakia from 1953 to 1957 .
Epaphroditus Ransom ( March 24 , 1798 -- November 11 , 1859 ) was the seventh Governor of Michigan and Michigan Supreme Court justice from the U.S. state of Michigan .
Alan G. Hevesi ( born January 31 , 1940 ) is a Democratic politician who served as a New York State Assemblyman from 1971 to 1993 , as New York City Comptroller from 1994 to 2001 , and as New York State Comptroller from 2003 to 2006 .
Vladislav Ardzinba ( Abkhaz : Владислав Арӡынба , Georgian : ვლადისლავ არძინბა ; 14 May 1945 -- 4 March 2010 ) was the first de facto President of Abkhazia .
Frank Kell Cahoon , Sr . ( June 20 , 1934 -- January 30 , 2013 ) , was an oilman and natural gas entrepreneur from Midland , Texas , who was the only Republican member of the Texas House of Representatives in the regular 1965 legislative session .
Daniel François Malan ( Afrikaans pronunciation : ( ˈdɑːnijəl frɐnˈswɑː mɑːˈlɐn ) ; 22 May 1874 -- 7 February 1959 ) , more commonly known as D. F. Malan , was a South African politician who was the Prime Minister of South Africa from 1948 to 1954 .
Thomas Arundel ( 1353 -- 19 February 1414 ) was Archbishop of Canterbury in 1397 and from 1399 until his death , an outspoken opponent of the Lollards .
Gabriel Bouvery ( died 1572 ) was a French bishop of Angers , successor to Jean V Olivier who died 12 April 1540 .
Juan Bautista Egusquiza Isasi ( 25 August 1845 , Asunción -- 24 August 1902 ) was President of Paraguay 25 November 1894 -- 25 November 1898 .
Arthur Pue Gorman ( March 11 , 1839 -- June 4 , 1906 ) was a United States Senator from Maryland , serving from 1881 to 1899 and from 1903 to 1906 .
Juan Bautista Pérez ( 20 December 1869 -- 7 May 1952 ) , was a Venezuelan lawyer , magistrate , and politician who served as President of Venezuela between 1929 until 1931 .
John Leigh Dardenne , Jr. , known as Jay Dardenne ( born February 6 , 1954 ) , served as the 53rd Lieutenant Governor of Louisiana , from 2010 to 2016 .
Dr. Gabriel Terra Leivas ( August 1 , 1873 -- September 15 , 1942 ) was the President of Uruguay from 1931 to 1938 .
Samuel David Ferguson ( January 1 , 1842 -- August 2 , 1916 ) was the first Black person to be elected a bishop of the Episcopal Church in the United States of America .
Francis Tukey ( 1814 - November 27 , 1867 ) was the City Marshal of Boston , Massachusetts from 1846 to 1852 and a member of the California State Assembly .
Hōjō Tsunetoki ( 北条 経時 , 1224 -- May 17 , 1246 ) was the fourth Shikken ( 1242 - -1246 ) of the Kamakura shogunate .
Agostino Falivene born from Giffoni Valle Piana in the province of Salerno , of the Order of the Servants of Maria , was Roman Catholic bishop of the island of Capri from the 25 September 1528 to the 24 April 1534 in that Pope Paul III transfers it to the island of Ischia where he died in 1548 .
Jimmie Lou Fisher ( born December 31 , 1941 ) is the longest serving Arkansas State Treasurer in Arkansas history , grew up in Paragould , Arkansas .
Samuel Albert LeBlanc , III , known as Sam A. LeBlanc , III ( born November 12 , 1938 ) , is a lawyer from St. Francisville in West Feliciana Parish , Louisiana , who is a Democratic former member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from District 86 in Jefferson and Orleans parishes .
Joseph A. Presel is an American diplomat and the former United States Ambassador to Uzbekistan .
Joan Maetsuycker ( 14 October 1606 -- 24 January 1678 ) was the Governor of Zeylan during the Dutch period in Ceylon and Governor - General of the Dutch East Indies from 1653 to 1678 .
Hans Göran Persson ( Swedish pronunciation : ( ˈʝœːran ˈpæːʂɔn ) ; born 20 January 1949 ) served as Prime Minister of Sweden from 1996 to 2006 and was leader of the Swedish Social Democratic Party from 1996 to 2007 .
William T. Bonniwell , Jr. was a member of the Wisconsin State Assembly , the Minnesota Senate and the Minnesota House of Representatives .
Sebkay ( alternatively Sebekay or Sebekāi ) was an ancient Egyptian pharaoh during the Second Intermediate Period , likely belonging to the 13th Dynasty .

Llewelyn Sherman Adams ( January 8 , 1899 -- October 27 , 1986 ) was an American politician , best known as White House Chief of Staff for President Dwight D. Eisenhower , the culmination of an 18-year political career that also included a stint as Governor of New Hampshire .

Clubiona is a large spider genus that occurs almost worldwide , although in South America , it is only found in Chile .

Crowea saligna is widely cultivated due to its attractive flowers that appear when most other species are dormant .

Bunomys is a genus of rodent from Sulawesi and Butung Island .
Bufo tuberculatus , commonly known as the Qinghai Lake toad or round - warted toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Procellariiformes is an order of seabirds that comprises four families : the albatrosses , petrels and shearwaters , storm petrels , and diving petrels .
Nebria is a genus of ground beetle native to the Palearctic , the Near East and North Africa .

Anomalomyidae is a family of extinct muroid rodents from Europe .
Miguashaiidae is an extinct family of prehistoric coelacanth fishes which lived during the Devonian period .
Paterinata is an extinct class of Paleozoic Era Linguliform brachiopod .

Chaetosiphon fragaefolii , the strawberry aphid , is a bug species in the genus Chaetosiphon found in the United States ( Arizona ) , Argentina and Chile .
Gueragama is an extinct genus of iguanian lizard from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .
Lophocolea heterophylla , the variable - leaved crestwort , is a liverwort species belonging to the order Jungermanniales , which is the largest liverwort order .
The Tonnidae are a family of medium - sized to very large sea snails , known as the tun shells .

Xyloiuloidea is an extinct superfamily of millipedes known from the Lower Devonian through the Upper Pennsylvanian of Europe and North America .
Monkey beetles are scarab beetles , a group of several genera within the tribe Hopliini .

Rubus thibetanus , sometimes known as ghost bramble , is a species of deciduous shrub in the genus Rubus , native to western China , where the local Chinese name may be translated into English as Tibetan dewberry .

Philodromus simoni is a spider species found in Spain and Algeria .
The type species is Batrachognathus volans .

Acer pentaphyllum ( 五小叶枫 wu xiao ye feng ) is a very rare , endangered maple species endemic to southwestern Sichuan in China , at altitudes of 2300 - -2900 meters .
The bird order Casuariiformes has four surviving members : the three species of cassowary , and the only remaining species of emu .
Eurhinosaurus ( ' well - nosed lizard ' ) is an extinct genus of ichthyosaur from the Early Jurassic ( Toarcian ) of Europe ( England , Germany , Benelux , France & Switzerland ) .
Sidalcea diploscypha is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name fringed checkerbloom .

The Sapphire Flutterer , ( Rhyothemis triangularis ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Farlowella martini is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it occurs in the coastal rivers draining into the Caribbean Sea .
Colura is a genus of epiphytic liverworts and consists of approximately 60 species that are distributed mostly in the tropics .

Polypedates is a genus of frogs in the family Rhacophoridae , the shrub frogs and Paleotropic tree frogs .
Correa reflexa var . speciosa , also known as eastern correa , is a variety of Correa reflexa , a shrub native to Australia .
Lasiosticha thermochroa is a species of snout moth in the genus Lasiosticha .
Carabus montivagus is a species of black coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Albania , Bulgaria , Greece , Hungary , Italy , Romania , Slovakia , and all of the republics of the former Yugoslavia .
Mesojassoides is a genus of extinct leaf hopper from the Late Cretaceous , approximately 70 - 66 million years ago , Fox Hills Formation .
Achnatherum latiglume is a species of grass known by the common names wide - glumed needlegrass and Sierra needlegrass .
Aecidium amaryllidis is a species of fungus in the Pucciniales order .
Cephalopholis is a genus of fish in the Serranidae family .
Lamellodynerus is an afrotropical genus of potter wasps with a single species Lamellodynerus nigrofulvus .
