Retrophyllum minus , the bois bouchon , is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae .
Aegiceras corniculatum , commonly known as Black Mangrove , River Mangrove or Khalsi , is a species of shrub or tree mangrove in the Myrsine family ( or Primrose family ) with a distribution in coastal and estuarine areas ranging from India through South East Asia to southern China , New Guinea and Australia .
Deltocephalus is a leafhopper genus in the sub family Deltocephalinae .
Geranium potentilloides is a species of geranium known by the common name cinquefoil geranium .
Lepadicyathus mendeleevi is a species of clingfish endemic to the reefs around Papua New Guinea .
Niobichthys ferrarisi is the only species of the monotypic genus Niobichthys of loricariid catfish ( order Siluriformes ) .
Monascus is a genus of mold .
The Plecoptera are an order of insects , commonly known as stoneflies .
Synxenidae is a family of bristly millipedes ( Polyxenida ) .
Epigynum auritum is a plant species in the genus Epigynum .
Agnostida is an order of arthropod which first developed near the end of the Early Cambrian period and thrived during the Middle Cambrian .
Sarcochilus fitzgeraldii , commonly known as the Ravine Orchid , is a species of orchid endemic to Australia , where it is found from southeastern Queensland to northeastern New South Wales .
Juncus covillei is a species of rush known by the common name Coville 's rush .
Callionymus scabriceps is a species of dragonet found in the Pacific waters of the Philippines and possibly also from Taiwan .
Phasianella australis , common names the Australian pheasant , painted lady , and pheasant snail , is a medium - sized to large species of sea snail with a calcareous operculum and a colorfully patterned shell , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Phasianellidae .
Rubus saxatilis or stone bramble is a species of bramble widespread across Europe and Asia from Iceland and Spain east as far as China .
Vismia jefensis is a species of flowering plant in the Hypericaceae family .
Encelia actoni , also known by the common names Acton brittlebush and Acton encelia , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Lactarius xanthogalactus , commonly known as the yellow - staining milkcap is a poisonous species of fungus in the family Russulaceae .
Byblia is a genus of nymphalid butterfly , commonly called Jokers , found in the Africa and the Indian subcontinent .
Uroplatus guentheri is a species of nocturnal gecko , which is endemic to Madagascar .
Diplocirrus glaucus is a species of marine polychaete found in ocean bottoms often consisting of mud , sand , shells or gravel .
Lewisia leeana ( orth.var . L. leana ) is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name quill - leaf lewisia .
Diplocardia longa is a species of earthworm native to North America .
Xerosecta adolfi is species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Purpuradusta minoridens , common name : the Small - toothed Cowry , is a species of tropical sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae .
Diplocardia is a genus of North American ( USA , Mexico ) earthworms with 52 - 57 known species that is remarkably similar to Australian Diplotrema Spencer , 1900 .
Poa pratensis , commonly known as Kentucky bluegrass , smooth meadow - grass , or common meadow - grass , is a perennial species of grass native to Europe , Asia , North America , and northern Africa .
Carmichaelia ( New Zealand Brooms ) is a genus of 24 plant species belonging to Fabaceae , the legume family .
Smilax glabra , the Chinaroot , tufuling ( 土茯苓 ) or sarsaparilla , is a plant species in the genus Smilax .
Saxifraga spathularis , the St Patrick's - cabbage , is a species of saxifrage native to the Portugal , Ireland and Spain .
The Sunda bush warbler ( Horornis vulcania ) is a species of bird in the Cettiidae family .
Euthynnus affinis , the kawakawa or mackerel tuna , is a species of ray - finned bony fish in the family Scombridae , or mackerel family .
The Nitrosopumilales are an order of the Archaea class Thermoprotei .
Omobranchus fasciolatus , the Arab blenny or barred Arab blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean .
Gasterophilus haemorrhoidalis ( also called nose bot ) is a species of the genus Gasterophilus that lays eggs on the lips and around the mouth of horses , mules and donkey , but also reindeer .
Wiedomys is a genus of South American rodents in the family Cricetidae .
Delphinium depauperatum is a species of larkspur known by the common names slim larkspur and dwarf larkspur .
Paracallionymus costatus , the Ladder dragonet , is a species of dragonet found along the southern coast of Africa from Namibia to Mozambique where it occurs at depths of from 55 to 400 metres ( 180 to 1,312 ft ) .
Undulatodoliops undulatofasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Undulatodoliops .
It consists of only one species , Habrophila compseuta , which is found in New Zealand .
Eleoscytalopus is a genus of tapaculos found in lowland Atlantic forest of eastern Brazil .
Centaurea bella is a species of Centaurea found in Anatolia and Transcaucasia .
Beishanichthys is an extinct genus of scanilepiform bony fish which existed in Gansu Province , China during the early Triassic period .
Polygala subspinosa is a species of flowering plant in the milkwort family known by the common name spiny milkwort .
Symphyotrichum eatonii ( formerly Aster eatonii ) is a species of aster known by the common name Eaton 's aster .
Pethia meingangbii is a species of cyprinid native to Manipur , India .
The Chacoan tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys dorsalis ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Trichroa oberthuri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichroa .
Physalis coztomatl is a species of Physalis genus of plants .
Symphyotrichum greatae ( formerly Aster greatae ) is a species of aster known by the common name Greata 's aster .
Banara vanderbiltii is a rare species of plant in the willow family known by the common name palo de ramon .
Petalomyrmex ( from Greek petalos , `` flattened '' + myrmex , `` ant '' ) is a genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae .
Argiope protensa is a species of the spider genus Argiope .
Colomesus is a genus of pufferfishes confined to tropical South America .
Draba globosa is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names beavertip draba , round - fruited draba , and rockcress draba .
Discherodontus is a small genus of cyprinid fishes found in Southeast Asia .
Pediocactus despainii is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Despain 's cactus and San Rafael cactus .
Galbula hylochoreutes is an extinct species of jacamar , small birds of the order of Coraciiformes .
Helodermoides is an extinct genus of anguid lizards from the Oligocene of North America .
Coxoplectoptera or `` chimera wings '' is a primitive , extinct order of winged insects containing one family , Mickoleitiidae , discovered in 2007 .
Parapeleconus latefasciatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parapeleconus .
Lobelia puberula is similar to two other Lobelia species in to the Eastern United States , Lobelia inflata ( Indian tobacco ) and Lobelia siphilitica ( great lobelia ) ; all display the characteristic `` lip '' petal near the opening of the flower and the `` milky '' liquid the plant excretes .
Michaelophorus hodgesi is a species of moth in the genus Michaelophorus , known from Puerto Rico .
†Lamellidea nakadai was a species of air - breathing tropical land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
Vokesimurex rubidus , common name : the rose murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Pleuroctenium is a genus of very small trilobites , that lived during the Middle Cambrian , in what are today Canada ( Newfoundland and New Brunswick ) , Czech Republic , England and Wales , France , and Sweden .
Parnaibaia is a genus of coelacanth fish which lived during the Late Jurassic period .
Irenosaurus is a genus of choristodere , a type of amphibious reptile .
Thermomesochra reducta is a species of copepod in the family Canthocamptidae , and the only species in the genus Thermomesochra .
Sphegina is a genus of small , slender hoverflies associated with woodlands .
Capparis sandwichiana is a species of flowering plant in the Capparaceae family endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Pherotrichis is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1838 .
Anaspidacea is an order of crustaceans , comprising eleven genera in four families .
Tachypleus gigas , one of the four extant species of horseshoe crab , is found in shallow water in Southeast Asia at depths to 40 m ( 130 ft ) .
Griphognathus ( `` hook - jaw '' ) is an extinct genus of lungfish from the late Devonian period of Europe and Australia .
Melica montezumae , Montezuma melicgrass , is a grass species in the Poaceae family that can be found in Texas and Mexico .
Combretum paniculatum , the burning bush or forest flame - creeper , is a plant species in the genus Combretum found in Africa .
Pseudemoia is a genus of skinks native to southeastern Australia .
†Chilonopsis subtruncatus was a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Subulinidae .
Calopteryx haemorrhoidalis is a species of damselfly in the family Calopterygidae known by the common names copper demoiselle and Mediterranean demoiselle .
Chrysopsis gossypina , called the Cottony goldenaster , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Grindelia oolepis , the plains gumweed , is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Anthanassa is a genus of South American butterflies of the Nymphalidae family found from the USA to South America .
Penicillium brefeldianum is an anamorph fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces Brefeldin A a fungal metabolite .
Brassolis is a genus of Neotropical butterflies in the Nymphalidae family .
Hypsognathus ( ' high jaw ' ) is an extinct genus of procolophonid parareptile from the Late Triassic of New Jersey and Connecticut .
Aackia is a genus of springtails in the family Isotomidae .
Carabus pedemontanus maurinensis is a subspecies of black - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that is endemic to France .
Cryptolepis sinensis is a plant species in the genus Cryptolepis , native to Taiwan , China ( Guangdong , Guangxi , Guizhou , Hainan , Yunnan ) and southeast Asia ( Cambodia , India , Indonesia , Malaysia , Vietnam ) .
Pulsatilla vernalis ( spring pasqueflower , arctic violet , lady of the snows ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Ranunculaceae , native to mountainous habitats in Europe .
Anisochilus is a genus in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1830 .
Phycisphaerae is a class of aquatic bacteria Containing a single order Phycisphaerales .
Sarcochilus falcatus , commonly known as the Orange Blossom Orchid , is a species of orchid endemic to Australia , where it is found from Queensland to Victoria .
Centaur oakblue or dull oakblue ( Arhopala centaurus ) is a species of lycaenid or blue butterfly found in Asia .
Atherix ibis is a species of ' ibis flies ' belonging to the family Athericidae , a small family very similar to Rhagionidae ( Snipe Flies ) .
Tor sinensis is a species of mahseer native to the Mekong River .
Trochosuchidae is an extinct family of therocephalian therapsids from the Permian period .
Digitaria iburua is a grass species native to west and west - central tropical Africa , which is cultivated as a grain crop known as black fonio .
Phyllostegia waimeae is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Kauai phyllostegia .
Pantherophis gloydi , commonly known as the eastern foxsnake or eastern fox snake , is a species of foxsnake .
Carpilius maculatus common names seven - eleven crab , spotted reef crab , dark - finger coral crab , and large spotted crab , is a species of crab in the family Carpiliidae .
Nadezhdiella cantori is a species of beetle from Cerambycidae family .
Geckolepis maculata is a species of gecko that is commonly found in Madagascar .
Quercus rysophylla , the loquat leaf oak , is a Mexican species of oak in the red oak section ( Quercus section Lobatae ) .
Montia parvifolia is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common names littleleaf minerslettuce , small - leaved blinks and small - leafed montia .
Bursaria is a genus of large shrubs and small trees which are native to Australia .
Elephas celebensis or the Sulawesi dwarf elephant is an extinct species of elephant .
Tambacarnifex ( meaning `` Tambach butcher '' ) is an extinct genus of varanodontine synapsid known from the Early Permian Tambach Formation of Free State of Thuringia , central Germany .
Roombia truncata is a species of katablepharids , which are heterotrophic single - celled organisms .
Sonchella is a genus of Asian flowering plants in the dandelion family .
Heterosperma pinnatum , the wingpetal , is a New World species of plants in the sunflower family .
Dacryopinax elegans is a species of jelly fungus in the family Dacrymycetaceae .

Percichthys melanops is a species of temperate perch endemic to Chile , where it occurs in pre - Andean streams .
Allium kingdonii is a rare species of wild onion endemic to southeastern Tibet .

Amblyeleotris harrisorum is a species of goby currently only recorded from reefs around the island of Kiritimati in the Line Islands , Republic of Kiribati , in the central Pacific at a depth of around 32 metres ( 105 ft ) .
Nothrotheriops is a genus of Pleistocene ground sloth found in North America , from what is now central Mexico to the southern United States .
Rubia peregrina , the common wild madder , is a herbaceous perennial plant species belonging to the bedstraw and coffee family Rubiaceae .
Nalameryx is an extinct genus of lophiomerycid ruminant which existed in lower Chitarwata Formation , Pakistan during the middle Oligocene .

Senecio planiflorus is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae and is endemic to Chile .

Paraleiopus sumatranus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraleiopus .

The Mascarene coot ( Fulica newtonii ) is an extinct species of coot that inhabited the Mascarene islands of Mauritius and Réunion .
Papilio diophantus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Sumatra .

Rhinella amboroensis is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae that is endemic to the region of its type locality in the Carrasco Province ( Cochabamba Department ) of Bolivia and the adjacent Santa Cruz Department .
The Rio Purus titi ( Callicebus purinus ) is a species of titi , a type of New World monkey , endemic to Brazil .
Hypselorhachis is a genus of extinct reptile , possibly a ctenosauriscid archosaur related to Ctenosauriscus .
Asemonea tenuipes is a species of Salticidae ( jumping spiders ) which can be found on Andaman Islands and in such countries as Burma , India , Sri Lanka , and Thailand .

Myoporum insulare may be used as a fast - growing hedge or windbreak species which withstands coastal winds and drought .
Delpydora is a genus of plant in the Sapotaceae family described as a genus in 1897 .
Lepidium nanum , the dwarf pepperweed , is a plant species native to the US states of Nevada and Utah .

Trinomys is a genus of South American spiny rats in the family Echimyidae .
Bassipterus is a genus of prehistoric eurypterid from the Silurian period of North America .

Eupselia beatella is a species of the Oecophoridae family that occurs in Australia .
Riodinidae is the family of metalmark butterflies .
Acalypha wilderi was a species of spurge that was only known from forested habitats along the northern and western sides of Rarotonga in the Cook Islands , at elevations of 200 - -300 m. Very little is known about this species , but collections suggest it was a small shrub rarely exceeding 2 m in height .
Cheiromeles is a genus of bats in the family Molossidae , the free - tailed bats .
Calliophis melanurus , commonly known as the Indian coral snake , is a species of venomous elapid snake endemic to the Indian subcontinent .
Microglossa is a genus of Asian and African flowering plants in aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Shibataea is a genus of Chinese bamboo in the grass family .
Hoheria populnea , commonly known as New Zealand mallow , lacebark or houhere , is a species of flowering plant in the family Malvaceae , endemic to New Zealand .
Mactra is a genus of medium - sized marine bivalve mollusks or clams , commonly known as trough shells or duck clams .
The genus consists of only one species , Nepita conferta , which can be found in India and Ceylon .
Aulophyseter is an extinct genus of sperm whale from the Miocene formations of the West and East coasts of North America as well as the Patagonian region of South America .
Calathus rotundatus is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Portugal and Spain .
Spathidexia setipennis is a species of fly in the genus Spathidexia of the family Tachinidae .
Abies numidica ( Algerian fir ) is a species of fir , found only in Algeria , where it is endemic on Djebel Babor , the second - highest mountain ( 2,004 m ) in the Algerian Tell Atlas .
Murex altispira , also known as the Caltrop murex , is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
Sphaerocystis is a genus of green algae , specifically of the class Chlorophyceae .
Xyelacyba myersi , the gargoyle cusk , is a species of cusk - eel found in the oceans at depths of from 984 to 2,500 metres ( 3,228 to 8,202 ft ) .
Amanita altipes , also called the yellow long - stem Amanita , is a species of agaric fungus found on soil in coniferous ( Abies , Picea ) and broadleaved ( Betula , Quercus , Salix ) woodland in southwestern China up to an altitude of 4,000 metres ( 13,000 ft ) .
Bryocella elongata is a bacterium , a type species of genus Bryocella .
Hiskatherium is an extinct genus of small ground sloth from the Miocene of Bolivia .

Ammodytoides is a genus of sand lances native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .

Harpalus serripes is a species of black coloured ground beetle which can be found in Palaearctic and the Near East .

Senecio ertterae is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Ertter 's ragwort .
Cystiscus viridis is a species of very small sea snail that around the coast of Australia .

Abutilon eremitopetalum , commonly known as the Hidden - petaled Abutilon or Hiddenpetal Indian Mallow , is a species of flowering shrub in the mallow family , Malvaceae .
Buddleja iresinoides is a species endemic to the rocky hillsides and stream banks of Bolivia and northern Argentina at altitudes from 300 to 1500 m. The species was correctly identified as a Buddleja and named by Hosseus in 1924 .
Austrocochlea zeus , common name the dory austrocochlea , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The genus name Achillobator means ' Achilles hero ' and is derived from Achilles , a famous ancient Greek warrior who fought in the Trojan War , and the Mongolian word baatar , anciently bagatur , which means ' hero ' .

Olea woodiana , known commonly as the Forest olive or black ironwood ( Afrikaans : Bosolienhout ) , is an African tree species belonging to the olive family ( Oleaceae ) .
The single member ( species ) of this genus , Phytala elais , the Giant Forest Blue , is found in Sierra Leone , Liberia , Ivory Coast , Ghana , Nigeria , Cameroon , Gabon , the Republic of Congo , the Democratic Republic of Congo , Sudan and Uganda .
Scarabaeus satyrus is one of the Old World dung beetle species .
Gobiopterus is a genus of gobies native to fresh , marine and brackish waters of the coastal areas around the Indian and Pacific oceans .
Caribeginella is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Marginellidae , the margin shells
Ostorhinchus cookii , common names Cook 's cardinalfish , Cook 's soldierfish , blackbanded cardinal , blackbanded cardinalfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Apogonidae .
Sisyrinchium platense is a species of flowering plant in the Iridaceae family .
†Carelia tenebrosa was a species of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Amastridae and superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Allium paniculatum , common name pale garlic or Mediterranean onion , is a Eurasian species of wild onion with a range extending from Portugal to Kazakhstan .
Sepia chirotrema is a species of cuttlefish native to the southern Indo - Pacific , specifically from Investigator Strait , southern Australia ( 35 ° 25′S 137 ° 22′E ) to Dirk Hartog Island , western Australia ( 25 ° 45′S 113 ° 03′E ) .
The Andrenidae ( commonly known as mining bees ) are a large , nearly cosmopolitan family of solitary , ground - nesting bees .
Apomyelois decolor , the Caribbean dried fruit moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Apomyelois .
Cilnia chopardi is a species of praying mantis in the genus Cilnia in the order Mantodea .
Castilleja latifolia is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name Monterey Indian paintbrush .
Otopleura glans , common name the acorn pyram , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Megasticus oberthuri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Megasticus .
Chanodichthys abramoides is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Chanodichthys .
Libelloides coccajus , the `` owly sulphur '' , is an owlfly species belonging to the family Ascalaphidae , subfamily Ascalaphinae .
Incilius pisinnus ( common name : Michoacan toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Placidochromis hennydaviesae is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from the southern portions of the lake .
Propterus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish of the Solnhofen Plattenkalk .
Dendrobium capra is a species of orchid endemic to the Island of Java in Indonesia .
Phacelurus is a genus of African and Eurasian plants in the grass family .
Ulvales is an order of green algae .
Chorizanthe polygonoides is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name knotweed spineflower .
Eresus cinnaberinus and Eresus niger are names formerly used for a group of spiders in the genus Eresus now divided into three species , E. kollari , E. sandaliatus and E. moravicus .
Calonectria ( anamorph Cylindrocladium ) is a genus of ascomycete fungi .
Candoia carinata , known commonly as the Pacific Ground Boa or the Pacific Keel - scaled Boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .
Cystosoma is a genus of cicada in of the Cicadinae subfamily native to Australia .
Metanephrops australiensis , commonly known as Australian scampi or the northwest lobster , is a species of lobster .
Gracixalus quyeti is a species of Shrub frog from Vietnam .
Galium glaucophyllum , the Sardinian Bedstraw , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Zabrus chalceus is a species of ground beetle in the Eutroctes subgenus that can be found in Armenia and Turkey .
Crossandra infundibuliformis ( firecracker flower ) , is a species of flowering plant in the family Acanthaceae , native to southern India and Sri Lanka .
Glossotherium ( literally `` Tongue Beast '' ) was a genus of ground sloth .
Pomatiopsidae is a family of small , mainly freshwater snails , ( some also occur in other habitats ) that have gills and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Rissooidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Mimulus rubellus is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name little redstem monkeyflower .
Barbus balcanicus , the Danube barbel ( or large - spot barbel ) , is a species of freshwater fish widespread in southeastern Europe .
Phyllidiopsis fissurata is a species of sea slug , specifically a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phyllidiidae .
Neomyia is a genus from the fly family Muscidae .
Goniastrea favulus , the lesser star coral , is a species of stony coral in the family Merulinidae .
Alismatidae is a botanical name at the rank of subclass .
The Pavoraja pseudonitida ( common name : false peacock skate ) is a species of fish in Rajidae family .
Felidae is the family of cats .
Arrhenotoides dubouzeti is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Arrhenotoides .
Helianthus praetermissus is a rare and probably extinct North American species of sunflower , with the common names New Mexico sunflower and `` lost sunflower . ''
Lindholmiola spectabilis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Helicodontidae .
Trifolium microdon is a species of clover known by the common name thimble clover .
Hyalomma is a genus of hard - bodied ticks , common in Asia , Europe , and North Africa .
Etelis is a genus of snappers mostly native to the Indian and Pacific oceans with one species ( E. oculatus ) native to the western Atlantic Ocean .
Corymbia haematoxylon , formerly known as Eucalyptus haematoxylon , is a species of eucalypt native to southwestern Australia .
Forbestra is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Fox in 1967 .
Orthetrum glaucum is an Asian dragonfly species , common across much of tropical and subtropical Asia , and capable of thriving in disturbed habitats .
The tribe Epidendreae of the Orchidaceae comprises six subtribes :
Oliva bulbosa , common name the swollen olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Heteromycteris is a genus of small soles found in salt and brackish water .
Orites revolutus , also known as Narrow - Leaf Orites , is a Tasmanian endemic plant species in the family Proteaceae .
Philydrella is a small genus of flowering plants described as a genus with this name in 1878 .
Prolongoa is a genus of Spanish plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family .
Blasia pusilla is the only species in the liverwort genus Blasia .
Calathea makoyana ( peacock plant , cathedral windows ) is a species of plant belonging to the genus Calathea in the family Marantaceae , native to eastern Brazil .
Sepia bidhaia is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean , specifically the waters off the Great Barrier Reef ( 17 ° 20′S 146 ° 41.5′E to 22 ° 07′S 153 ° 19′E ) .
Japalura tricarinata is a species of agamid lizard endemic to Asia .
Siamosaurus ( meaning `` Siamese lizard '' ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur from Early Cretaceous Thailand .
Nyssa sinensis ( Chinese tupelo ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cornaceae ( or Nyssaceae ) , native to China and Vietnam .
Cyathea javanica is a species of tree fern native to western Java and Sumatra , in Indonesia .
Ariamnes uwepa is a species of spider from the family Theridiidae .
Ranunculus pusillus is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup genus known by the common name low spearwort .
Packera greenei is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name flame ragwort .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Cyanopulvis australiensis .
The Bengal tiger , also called the royal Bengal tiger ( Panthera tigris tigris ) , is the most numerous tiger subspecies .
Trichosporon is a genus of anamorphic fungi in the family Trichosporonaceae .
Trichilia triacantha , the bariaco , is a species of plant in the Meliaceae family .
Carex microptera is a species of sedge known by the common name smallwing sedge .
Myctophum asperum , common name the prickly lanternfish , is a species of deep sea fish in the family Myctophidae , the `` lanternfish '' .
Amietophrynus chudeaui , the Bata marsh toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Nymphophilus minckleyi is a species of very small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Dendrobium tetragonum , the Common Spider Orchid , is a species of orchid , also known as the Rectangular - bulbed Dendrobium or Tree Spider Orchid .
Ranunculus orthorhynchus is a species of buttercup known by the common name straightbeak buttercup .
Physcomitrium is a genus of mosses , commonly called urn moss , that includes about 80 species and has a cosmopolitan distribution .
Dekeyseria scaphirhyncha is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Rio Negro basin .
Pantheidae is a family of Lepidoptera .
Andrena marginata is a species of the sand bee ( Andrena ) genus .
Australornis ( Latin : `` southern bird '' ) is a genus of extinct seabird discovered in New Zealand .
Senna odorata , fragrant senna , spreading cassia or southern cassia , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family .
Agathaeromys is an extinct genus of oryzomyine rodents from the Pleistocene of Bonaire , West Indies .
Lachneratus phasmaticus also known as the Phantom cardinalfish , is a species of fish in the family Apogonidae , the cardinalfishes .
Cerithiopsis fayalensis is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from the southwestern coast of Apulia , Italy .
Doryrhamphus japonicus , or the honshu pipefish , is a species of flagtail pipefish from the genus Doryrhamphus that occurs in the Western Pacific Ocean .
Nicotiana alata is a species of tobacco .
Mantoida maya , common name little Yucatán mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Mexico and the U.S. state of Florida .
Erica arborea ( tree heath ) is a species of flowering plant ( angiosperms ) in the heather family , Ericaceae .
Acantholycosa sterneri is a species of wolf spider found in Mongolia and southern Siberia .
Ernodea littoralis , the golden creeper , beech creeper , coughweed , or coughbush , is a species of flowering plants in the coffee family , Rubiaceae , endemic to Central America and the Caribbean region .
The Haplosclerida are an order of demosponges .
Titanacris albipes is a species of grasshopper in the family Romaleidae .
Oligoryzomys griseolus , also known as the grizzled colilargo or the grayish pygmy rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oligoryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Angophora leiocarpa is a tree species that is native to eastern Australia .
Vectidraco ( meaning `` dragon from the Isle of Wight '' ) , is a genus of azhdarchoid pterosaur from the Lower Cretaceous of England .
Pyramidula umbilicata is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidulidae .
Plagiorchis elegans is a species of parasitic trematodes ( flukes ) in the genus Plagiorchis .
Eurema irena was treated as a subspecies of Eurema simulatrix , but formally raised to full species status by Yata in 1994 .
Appalachiosaurus ( /ˌæpəˌleɪtʃioʊˈsɔːrəs/ ap - ə - LAY - chee - o - SAWR - əs ; `` Appalachian lizard '' ) is a genus of tyrannosauroid theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous Period of eastern North America .
Cnidaria ( /naɪˈdɛəriə/ ) is a phylum containing over 10,000 species of animals found exclusively in aquatic ( freshwater and marine ) environments : they are predominantly marine species .
Clavaria fragilis , commonly known as fairy fingers , white worm coral , or white spindles , is a species of fungus in the family Clavariaceae .
Glyptocrinus is an extinct genus of sea lily that lived from the Middle Ordovician to the Early Silurian ( 471.8 - 436.0 Ma ) .
The Citharidae are a small family of flounders .
Iris missouriensis ( syn . I. montana ) is a hardy flowering rhizomatous species of the genus Iris , in the family Iridaceae .
Bolitoglossa mombachoensis ( Spanish : Salamandra De Mombacho ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .

Callicorixa praeusta is a species of Corixidae or water boatman , in the order Hemiptera .

Lotagnostus is a genus of very small trilobites in the order Agnostida , which lived on the outer shelfs worldwide , during the late Upper Cambrian .
Spuleria is a genus of moths of the Elachistidae family .
Boiga barnesii is a species of cat snake found in Sri Lanka known as the Barnes ' cat snake in English and panduru mapila-පදුරු මාපිලා in Sinhala .
Amnicola limosus , common name the mud amnicola , is a species of very small aquatic snail , an operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .

Australosyodon is an extinct genus of dinocephalian therapsid from the middle Permian of South Africa .
Discogobio is a genus of cyprinid fish that are found in eastern Asia .
Sinocyclocheilus anatirostris is a species of cyprinid .
Penicillium hetheringtonii is a species of the genus of Penicillium which is named after A.C. Hetherington .
Thylacodes aotearoicus is a species of sea snail , a worm snail or worm shell , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Vermetidae , the worm snails .
Seriatopora caliendrum is a species of colonial stony coral in the family Pocilloporidae .
The Asiatic glassfishes are a family , Ambassidae , of freshwater and marine fishes in the order Perciformes .
Peltephilus ferox , the horned armadillo , was a species of dog - sized , armadillo - like xenarthran mammal which first inhabited Argentina during the Oligocene epoch , and became extinct in the Miocene epoch .
Mesarthropterus wasmanni is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Mesarthropterus .
Carex hystericina is a species of sedge known by the common names bottlebrush sedge and porcupine sedge .
Lebiasina is a genus of fishes found in tropical South America , with eighteen currently recognized species :
Cycas badensis is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to Australia , in the extreme north of Queensland , where it is endemic on Badu Island in the Torres Strait Islands .
Erigeron uintahensis is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Uinta fleabane .
Streptomyces avidinii is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which produces streptavidin .
Argyrophenga antipodum , otherwise known by its common names , the Common tussock , or the Tussock ringlet , is a species of butterfly which can be commonly found in the South Island of New Zealand .
Apistogramma is a genus of approximately a hundred species of fish from the family Cichlidae .
Bombus erzurumensis is a species of bumblebee found in Turkey ( north - eastern Anatolia ) and northern Iran .
Pleosporaceae is a family of sac fungi .
Acartiidae is a family of calanoid copepods distinguishable by the rostral margin not being extended .
Colwellia demingiae is a psychrophilic Antarctic bacterial species with the ability to synthesize docosahexaenoic acid .
Delclosia is an extinct genus of shrimp in the order Decapoda , containing two species .
Macroscelesaurus is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsid from the Late Permian of South Africa .

Callavia is an extinct , monotypic genus of trilobite arthropods .
The earliest remains of Prodeinotherium come from Kenya , where two deposits preserving the genus date to 22.5 and 19.5 million years ago according to one 1978 study .
Johannesteijsmannia is a genus of four species of palms found in tropical rainforests of southern Thailand , Malaysia and Indonesia .
Lobalopex is an extinct genus of biarmosuchian therapsid or mammal - like `` reptile '' belonging to the family Burnetiidae .
Helladotherium is an extinct genus of Sivatherine Giraffid from Europe , Africa , and Asia during the Miocene .
Mikania is a genus of about 450 species in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Tanycolagreus is a genus of coelurid theropod from the Late Jurassic of North America .
Atriplex vesicaria , commonly known as Bladder Saltbush , is a species of saltbush endemic to Australia .

Puya ferruginea is a plant species in the genus Puya .
Gnaphosa corticola is a ground spider species found in France .
Amaurobius occidentalis is a spider species found in Portugal , Spain and France .
Elephant birds are members of the extinct family Aepyornithidae .
Japananus hyalinus , the Japanese Maple Leafhopper , is a species of leafhoppers of the subfamily Deltocephalinae , tribus Opsiini ( formerly placed in tribus Scaphytopiini ) .
Minicynodon ( meaning ' small Cynodon ' ) is a genus of carnivorous brasilodontid cynodont from the Late Triassic period .
Gymnophryxe modesta is a Palaearctic species of tachinid flies in the genus Gymnophryxe of the family Tachinidae .
Pilgrimella is an extinct early Eocene genus of anthracobunid , a group of stem perissodactyls ( formerly classified with proboscideans ) .
Antelope squirrels or antelope ground squirrels of the genus Ammospermophilus are sciurids found in the desert and dry scrub areas of south - western United States and northern Mexico .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Semiomphalina leptoglossoides , found in Papua New Guinea .
The Gounda mouse ( Mus goundae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Argonauticeras is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus that lived during the latter part of the Early Cretaceous , included in the Lytoceratida and found in lower and possibly middle Aptian marine sediments .
The Makatea fruit dove ( Ptilinopus chalcurus ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Nia vibrissa is a species of fungus in the order Agaricales .
Stenopelmatoidea is a superfamily of insects in the order Orthoptera ; in some older classifications this group was referred to as Gryllacridoidea .
Megalurulus , the thicketbirds , is a genus of songbirds .
The Australian plague locust is less gregarious than other locust species and swarms occur in a continuum from dense swarms through a range of densities down to scattered adults .
Hisonotus acuen is a species of armored catfish from the Xingu River in Brazil .
Heterometrus laoticus is a scorpion species found in peaty areas of Vietnam and Laos .
Plesiobaena is an extinct genus of turtle which existed in the Belly River Formation , Canada during the late Cretaceous period ( Campanian age ) .
Alternaria dauci is included in the porri species group of Alternaria , which is classified for having large conidium and a long , slender filiform beak .
Protoginella is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Colobosauroides is a small genus in the family of spectacled lizards .

The Roque Chico de Salmor giant lizard ( Gallotia simonyi simonyi ) was the nominate subspecies of the lacertid ( wall lizard ) Gallotia simonyi .
Mauritia mappa , common name the map cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Stranvaesia davidiana , the Chinese photinia , is a species of shrub grown as an ornamental plant .
Gyraulus nedyalkovi is a species of small , mostly air - breathing , freshwater snail , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Temburongia is a genus of bamboo from the Sultanate of Brunei on the Island of Borneo .

Spartina densiflora is a species of grass known by the common name denseflower cordgrass .
Achatinella buddii is an extinct species of land snail , a gastropod in the Achatinellidae family .

Cyperus odoratus is a species of sedge known by the common names fragrant flatsedge and rusty flatsedge .
Mammillaria longimamma is a species of cactus from Hidalgo and Querétaro , Mexico .
Gracilepteryx is an extinct genus of moths within the family Eolepidopterigidae , containing one species , Gracilepteryx pulchra , which is known from the Crato Formation in Brazil .
Trichonympha is a genus of parabasalid protists that live in the intestines of many , if not most , termite species .
Rhynchochydorus australiensis is a species of crustacean in the family Chydoridae .
Bambusa tulda or Indian timber bamboo is considered to be one of the most useful of bamboo species .
Mastigoteuthis magna is a species of whip - lash squid , characterised by a lack of photophores .
Streptomyces caelestis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Utah in the USA .
Desmids ( Gr . desmos , bond or chain ) are an order ( Desmidiales ) in the Charophyta , a division of green algae that forms a sister group to the land plants ( Embryophyta ) .
Hyalimax maillardi is a species of air - breathing succineid land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
Characiosiphon is a genus of green algae , in the family Characiosiphonaceae .
Hoplolatilus is a genus of tilefishes native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Neokochia californica ( syn . Bassia californica , Kochia californica ) is a species of flowering plant in the subfamily Camphorosmoideae of the amaranth family known by the common name rusty molly .
The Columbian sharp - tailed grouse ( Tympanuchus phasianellus columbianus ) is a subspecies of sharp - tailed grouse native to the Western United States and British Columbia .
Styphelia tameiameiae , known as pūkiawe or maiele in the Hawaiian language , is a species of flowering plant in the heather family , Ericaceae , that is native to the Hawaiian and Marquesas Islands .
Breyeriana cistransandina is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Breyeriana .

Virola surinamensis , known commonly as baboonwood and chalviande , is a species of flowering plant in the family Myristicaceae .
Hemiscyllium halmahera or Halmahera epaulette shark is a species of bamboo shark from Indonesia .
Phaonia lugubris is a species of fly which is distribution across parts the Palaearctic .
Stagetillus opaciceps is a spider species of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) .
Holttumochloa is a genus of Malaysian bamboos in the grass family native to the hill forests of Peninsular Malaysia .
Ciliopagurus albatrossi is a species of hermit crab native to the Hawaiian region .
Penstemon acuminatus is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names sharpleaf penstemon and sand - dune penstemon .
Tacca ankaranensis is a species of flowering plant in the yam family Dioscoreaceae , which is endemic to Madagascar .
Neolamprologus modestus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it lives on rocky substrates in the southern portion of the lake .
Oncidium longicornu is a species of orchid occurring from Brazil to northeastern Argentina , where it is recorded from the provinces of Misiones and Corrientes .
Malus trilobata , the Lebanese wild apple , erect crab apple or three - lobed apple tree , is a species in the family Rosaceae in the genus Malus .

Ranunculidae is a subclass of plants used in some taxonomic systems and not others .
Trillium erectum , also known as red trillium , wake - robin , purple trillium , Beth root , or stinking Benjamin , is a species of flowering plant native to the east and north - east of North America .
The Many - flowered Grass - pink , Calopogon multiflorus , is a species of orchid .
Anelosimus kohi is a species of spider in the family Theridiidae .
Conus anemone , common name the anemone cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Arminidae is a family of sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Arminoidea .
The Sierra Leone free - tailed bat ( Mops brachypterus ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Liophlaeothrips is a genus of thrips in the family Phlaeothripidae .

Brithura is a genus of true crane fly .
Cudonia is a genus of fungi within the family Cudoniaceae .

Calliotropis spinulosa is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliotropidae .
Caulanthus major is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name slender wild cabbage .
Erysimum menziesii is a species of wallflower known by the common name Menzies ' wallflower .
Sinotectirostrum is a genus of brachiopod found in Paleozoic strata .
Chamaesipho is a genus of four - plated notochthamaline barnacles in the Pacific Ocean limited to Australia / New Zealand temperate waters .
Margarinotus brunneus is a species of beetles belonging to the family Histeridae .
Sicyopterus griseus , the Clown goby , is a species of goby endemic to India and Sri Lanka , where it is found in estuaries , blackwaters , and fresh waters .
Psaltoda harrisii , commonly known as the yellowbelly , is a species of cicada native to eastern Australia .
Lysiosepalum is a genus of plants in the family Sterculiaceae , endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Chrysomyza sericea is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Chrysomyza of the family Tephritidae .
Terpnomyia latifrons is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Terpnomyia of the family Ulidiidae .
Megacoelacanthus is an extinct genus of lobe - finned fish which lived during the Jurassic period .
Cambaroides schrenckii is a species of crayfish endemic to north - eastern China and Russia .
Silene polypetala ( syn . Silene catesbaei ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names eastern fringed catchfly and fringed campion .
Alloblennius frondiculus is a species of combtooth blenny ( family Blenniidae ) in the genus Alloblennius .
Hestina assimilis , or , the Red Ring Skirt , is a species of butterfly in the family Nymphalidae found in Asia .
Talipariti is a genus of plants in the mallow family Malvaceae .
Conus urashimanus , common name the Urashima cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Lydekkerinidae is a family of stereospondyl temnospondyls that lived in the Triassic period .
The Antarctic scallop ( Adamussium colbecki ) is the only species in the genus though its exact relationship to other members of the family is unclear .
Artemisia lactiflora , the white mugwort , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family , native to Western China .
Hypoptychus dybowskii , the Japanese sandlance , is a species of hypoptychid fish found in shallow salt water off the coasts of Japan and Sakhalin ( Russia ) as well as possibly occurring in South Korea and China .
Hippotragus is a genus of antelopes which includes three species :
Homorhynchus ( Greek for `` same snout '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish from the Eocene and Oligocene .
Terminalia eriostachya , the black mastic , is a species of flowering tree in the leadwood family , Combretaceae .
Aplochiton taeniatus is a species of amphidromous galaxiid native to Argentina and Chile in South America .
Telosphrantis is a genus of moths in the Choreutidae family , containing only one species , Telosphrantis aethiopica , which is known from Ethiopia .
Leptonetidae is a family of relatively primitive haplogyne ( lacking hardened external female genitalia ) spiders , which includes 15 genera and nearly 200 species .
Amorphosternoides vianai is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Amorphosternoides .
Opsopoeodus emiliae ( common name pugnose minnow ) is a species of cyprinid fish found in the eastern North America .
Nebria snowi is a species of ground beetle from the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Kuril Islands , Russia .
Puccinellia nutkaensis is a species of grass known by the common names Nootka alkaligrass and Alaska alkali grass .
Mimallonoidea is the superfamily of sack bearer moths , containing the single family Mimallonidae .
The genus includes only one species , Afrocoscinia aethiopica ( Kühne , 2010 ) , which is found in the arid regions of the western part of South Africa .
Neoarius is a genus of sea catfishes found on and around the island New Guinea and Australia .
Boletus is a genus of mushroom - producing fungi , comprising over 100 species .
Conorhynchos conirostris is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) .
Domiporta gloriola , common name : the glorious mitre , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Astyanacinus is a genus of characins from South America .
Cassipourea swaziensis ( Swazi onionwood , Afrikaans : Swazi - uiehout ) is a species of plant in the Rhizophoraceae family .
Penicillium osmophilum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from agricultural soil in Wageningen in the Netherlands
Zoneait ( pronounced `` zone - eight '' and meaning `` large tooth '' in the Kiowa language ) is an extinct genus of thalattosuchian crocodylomorph known from a single species , Zoneait nargorum , from the Middle Jurassic of Oregon .
Maytenus tenuispina is a Southern African shrub or small tree of about 2 m in height and one of about 120 species of Maytenus belonging to the family Celastraceae .
Hamamelis × intermedia ( hybrid witch hazel ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Hamamelidaceae .
Pardosa is a large genus of wolf spiders , with more than 500 described species that are found in all regions of the world .
Pseuderia is a genus of orchids consisting of about 20 species distributed from the Moluccas through New Guinea to Samoa , Fiji and Micronesia .
The Angulated dwarf gecko is a species of gecko native to southern Zaire and Tanzania .
Eirmocephala is a genus of Latin American plants in the evil tribe within the sunflower family .
Tectus niloticus , common name the commercial top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Verbascum densiflorum , the denseflower mullein or dense - flowered mullein , is a plant species in the genus Verbascum .
Scaphyglottis crurigera is a species of orchid found from Mexico ( Oaxaca , Chiapas ) to Ecuador .
Pseudochazara alpina ( Staudinger , 1878 ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
The Bolivian red howler ( Alouatta sara ) is a species of howler monkey , a type of New World monkey , endemic to Bolivia .
The Tonkin toad ( Bufo pageoti ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Mithrodia clavigera is a species of tropical starfish in the family Mithrodiidae .
Mesoglossus pygmaeus is a species of acorn worm in the family Harrimaniidae , which is found in Europe , precisely in British Isles .
Allium caesioides is a plant species found in the high mountains of India , Pakistan , Tajikistan and Afghanistan .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Tribulatia appendicospora .
Diaphoroplax biramosus is a rare species of chiton in the family Mopaliidae .
Campylomormyrus rhynchophorus is one of fourteen species of elephantfish in the genus Campylomormyrus .
Spironucleus is a genus of Diplomonad flagellates that inhabit the digestive tract of a variety of animal hosts .
Lepista personata ( also recognised as Lepista saeva , Clitocybe saeva and Tricholoma personatum , and commonly known as the field blewit and blue - leg ) is a species of fungus .
Thelephora palmata ( commonly known as the stinking earthfan or the fetid false coral ) is a species of clavarioid fungus in the family Thelephoraceae .
The Panama amazon , also known as the Panama yellow - headed amazon , ( Amazona ochrocephala panamensis ) is a subspecies of the yellow - crowned amazon , and is endemic to Panama ( including the Pearl Islands and Coiba ) and northwest Colombia .
Marasmius cladophyllus is a species of fungus in the family Marasmiaceae .
Sparganothis diluticostana , the Spring Dead - leaf Roller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Supramontana is a genus of land planarians from South America .
The nematoceran infraorder Psychodomorpha ( sometimes misspelled Psychomorpha - which is also the name of a genus of noctuid moths ) includes two common families , Psychodidae and Scatopsidae , and other very small , rare families .
Microhyla heymonsi ( commonly known as the dark - sided chorus frog or the Taiwan rice frog ) is a species of narrow - mouthed frog found in northeastern India , southern China , Taiwan , and Southeast Asia south to the Malay Peninsula and Sumatra as well as the Great Nicobar Island .
The Callistophytales was an order of mainly scrambling and lianescent plants found in the wetland `` coal swamps '' of Euramerica and Cathaysia .
The Buru mountain pigeon ( Gymnophaps mada ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Nanorana polunini ( common names : Langtang paa frog , Smith frog , Polunin 's paa frog , Polunin 's spiny frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Brigantiaea is a genus of lichens in the family Brigantiaeaceae .
Agapanthia gemella is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that is endemic to Cyprus .
Bombus pyrenaeus is a species of bumblebee belonging to the family Apidae .
Labeobarbus versluysii is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Cameroon in the Wouri , Sanaga and Nyong river basins .
Brachinus patruelis is a species of ground beetle in the Brachininae subfamily that is endemic to Massachusetts , United States .
Thunnus is a genus of ocean - dwelling ray - finned bony fish from the Scombridae ( Mackerel ) family .
Ostorhinchus parvulus is a species of saltwater fish in the Apogonidae family of order Perciformes that lives in Eastern Asia found along rocky reefs around bays .
Portea fosteriana is a species in the genus Portea .
The Boinae are a subfamily of boas found in Central and South America , Africa , and Southeast Asia ( Reunion Island , Mauritius , the Maluku Islands and New Guinea ) .
Hypericum canariense is a species of St. John's - wort known by the common name Canary Islands St. John's - wort .
Dyacopterus is a genus of megabats from south - east Asia .
Maiestas vetus is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that is indigenous to Australia and New Zealand .
Oeceoclades decaryana is a terrestrial orchid species of the genus Oeceoclades that is native throughout southern and southeastern Africa .
Cnaphalocrocis medinalis , the rice leafroller , is a species of moth of the Crambidae family .
Doridomorphidae is a taxonomic family of colorful sea slugs or nudibranchs .
Hoogerwerf 's rat ( Rattus hoogerwerfi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Margarites pilsbryi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae , .
Pristimantis is a very large frog genus distributed in the southern Caribbean ( Lesser Antilles ) and in Central and South America from Honduras to northern Argentina and southern Brazil .
Eulaema mocsaryi is a species of large - bodied bee in the tribe Euglossini , the orchid bees .
Peziza cerea , commonly known as the Cellar Cup is a species of Ascomycete fungus in the genus Peziza , family Pezizaceae .
Montserrat Figueras i García ( Catalan : ( munsəˈrat fiˈɣeɾəs i ɡərˈsi.ə ) ; 1942 - -2011 ) was a Spanish soprano who specialized in early music .
Otto Peter ( born 1931 ) is a Swiss classical baritone .
Olimpia Boronat ( 1859 or 1867 -- 1934 ) was an Italian operatic coloratura soprano , noted for her performances of the soprano roles in the bel canto repertory .
Raffaele Arié ( 22 August 1920 , Sofia - 17 March 1988 , Switzerland ) was a Bulgarian bass , particularly associated with the Italian and Russian repertories .
Julián Dobrski ( 31 December 1811 or 1812 , Nowe - 2 May 1886 , Warsaw ) was a Polish operatic tenor .
Wallace Brownlow ( 1861 -- September 1919 ) was an opera singer and actor of the Victorian era best known for baritone roles in the operas of Gilbert and Sullivan .
Bryn Terfel Jones CBE ( Welsh pronunciation : ( ˈbrɨn ˈtɛrvɛl ) ; born 9 November 1965 ) is a Welsh bass - baritone opera and concert singer .
Fanny Tacchinardi Persiani ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈfanːi takːiˈnardi perˈsjani ) ) ( 4 October 1812 -- 3 May 1867 ) was an Italian soprano particularly associated with bel canto composers , such as Rossini , Donizetti , Bellini , and early Verdi .
Éva Marton ( born June 18 , 1943 ) is a Hungarian dramatic soprano , particularly known for her operatic portrayals of Puccini 's Turandot and Tosca , and Wagnerian roles .
Latonia Moore ( born 1979 , in Houston , Texas ) is an American soprano .
Antonio Magini - Coletti ( 17 February 1855 -- 21 July 1912 ) was a leading Italian baritone who had a prolific career in Europe and the United States during the late 19th century and the early part of the 20th century .
Domenico de ' Panzacchi ( 1733 -- after 1805 ) was an Italian operatic tenor and the first Arbace in Mozart 's Idomeneo re di Creta .
Josephine Veasey ( born July 10 , 1930 ) is a British mezzo - soprano , particularly associated with Wagner and Berlioz roles .
Louise Tucker ( born 1956 ) is an English mezzo - soprano opera singer from Bristol , England .
Jolana Fogašová is a Slovak opera singer with the voice type of soprano .
Robert Leonhardt ( 1877 -- February 2 , 1923 ) was an operatic baritone who sang several notable roles with the New York Metropolitan Opera between 1913 and 1922 .
Emma Seehofer ( died 1912 ) was a German operatic contralto who was a principal artist at the Bavarian State Opera in Munich from 1854 to 1887 .
Franz Xaver Gerl ( 1764 - -1827 ) was a bass singer and composer of the classical era .
Giuseppe Ciccimarra ( 22 May 1790 -- 5 December 1836 ) was an Italian tenor , closely associated with Rossini roles .
Solange Michel ( November 27 , 1912 -- December 15 , 2010 ) was a French classical mezzo - soprano who sang in concerts , recitals , and operas from the 1930s to the 1970s .
Werner Güra ( born 1964 ) is a German classical tenor in opera , concert and Lied , also an academic teacher in Zurich .
Bruno Prevedi ( December 21 , 1928 in Revere , ( Mantua ) -- January 12 , 1988 in Milan ) was an Italian tenor , particularly associated with the Italian repertory .
Karel Burian ( also Carl Burrian ) ( 12 January 1870 -- 25 September 1924 ) was a renowned Czech operatic tenor who had an active international career spanning the 1890s to the 1920s .
Martha Sheil is an American operatic soprano who made her professional opera debut as the Contessa in Le nozze di Figaro at the New York City Opera under the baton of Julius Rudel .
Betty Fabila ( born 28 May 1929 ) is a retired Mexican soprano opera singer and biologist .
Alexander Kipnis ( February 13 ( O.S. February 1 ) 1891 -- May 14 , 1978 ) was a Ukrainian - born operatic bass .
Florence Foster Jenkins ( July 19 , 1868 -- November 26 , 1944 ) was an American socialite and amateur operatic soprano who was known and ridiculed for her lack of rhythm , pitch , and tone ; her aberrant pronunciation ; and her generally poor singing ability .
Jarmila Novotná ( September 23 , 1907 , in Prague -- February 9 , 1994 , in New York City ) was a celebrated Czech soprano and actress and , from 1940 to 1956 , a star of the Metropolitan Opera .
Gladys Kuchta ( 1915 - -1998 ) was an American operatic soprano who sang leading roles in opera houses world - wide including the Vienna State Opera , Royal Opera House , Bayreuth Festival , San Francisco Opera , and the Teatro Colón .
Cristina Iordachescu is a Romanian mezzo - soprano and pianist .
Leo Marian Vodička ( born 8 April 1950 ) is a Czech operatic tenor who has had an active international career since the early 1970s .
